{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "1CH"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["1 Chronicles \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The First Book of Chronicles \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["1 Chronicles \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["1Ch \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["The First Book of Chronicles \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 1:1"}, "Adam, Seth, Enosh, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 1:2"}, "Kenan, Mahalalel, Jared, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 1:3"}, "Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 1:4"}, "Nuh, Shem, Ham, and Japheth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 1:5"}, "The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech, and Tiras.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 1:6"}, "The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Diphath, and Togarmah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 1:7"}, "The sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Rodanim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 1:8"}, "The sons of Ham: Cush, Mizraim, Put, and Canaan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 1:9"}, "The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabta, Raama, Sabteca. The sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 1:10"}, "Cush became the father of Nimrod. He began to be a mighty one in the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 1:11"}, "Mizraim became the father of Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 1:12"}, "Pathrusim, Casluhim (where the Philistines came from), and Caphtorim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 1:13"}, "Canaan became the father of Sidon his firstborn, Heth, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 1:14"}, "the Jebusite, and the Amorite, the Girgashite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 1:15"}, "the Hivite, the Arkite, the Sinite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 1:16"}, "the Arvadite, the Zemarite, and the Hamathite. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 1:17"}, "The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, Aram, Uz, Hul, Gether, and Meshech.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 1:18"}, "Arpachshad became the father of Shelah, and Shelah became the father of Eber.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 1:19"}, "To Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg, for in his days the earth was divided; and his brother\u2019s name\nwas Joktan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 1:20"}, "Joktan became the father of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 1:21"}, "Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 1:22"}, "Ebal, Abimael, Sheba, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 1:23"}, "Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 1:24"}, "Shem, Arpachshad, Shelah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 1:25"}, "Eber, Peleg, Reu, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 1:26"}, "Serug, Nahor, Terah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 1:27"}, "Ibram (also called Ibrahim). \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 1:28"}, "The sons of Ibrahim: Is\u1e25\u0101q and Ismail. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 1:29"}, "These are their generations: the firstborn of Ismail, Nebaioth; then Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 1:30"}, "Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 1:31"}, "Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ismail.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 1:32"}, "The sons of Keturah, Ibrahim\u2019s concubine: she bore Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. The sons of\nJokshan: Sheba and Dedan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 1:33"}, "The sons of Midian: Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah. All these were the sons of Keturah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 1:34"}, "Ibrahim became the father of Is\u1e25\u0101q. The sons of Is\u1e25\u0101q: Esau and Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CH 1:35"}, "The sons of Esau: Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam, and Korah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CH 1:36"}, "The sons of Eliphaz: Teman, Omar, Zephi, Gatam, Kenaz, Timna, and Amalek.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CH 1:37"}, "The sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CH 1:38"}, "The sons of Seir: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CH 1:39"}, "The sons of Lotan: Hori and Homam; and Timna was Lotan\u2019s sister.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CH 1:40"}, "The sons of Shobal: Alian, Manahath, Ebal, Shephi, and Onam. The sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1CH 1:41"}, "The son of Anah: Dishon. The sons of Dishon: Hamran, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1CH 1:42"}, "The sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Jaakan. The sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1CH 1:43"}, "Now these are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom, before any king reigned over the children of Israel: Bela the\nson of Beor; and the name of his city was Dinhabah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "1CH 1:44"}, "Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "1CH 1:45"}, "Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "1CH 1:46"}, "Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad, who struck Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his place; and the name of\nhis city was Avith. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "1CH 1:47"}, "Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "1CH 1:48"}, "Samlah died, and Shaul of Rehoboth by the River reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "1CH 1:49"}, "Shaul died, and Baal Hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "1CH 1:50"}, "Baal Hanan died, and Hadad reigned in his place; and the name of his city was Pai: and his wife\u2019s name was Mehetabel, the\ndaughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "1CH 1:51"}, "Then Hadad died. The chiefs of Edom were: chief Timna, chief Aliah, chief Jetheth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "1CH 1:52"}, "chief Oholibamah, chief Elah, chief Pinon, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "1CH 1:53"}, "chief Kenaz, chief Teman, chief Mibzar, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "1CH 1:54"}, "chief Magdiel, and chief Iram. These are the chiefs of Edom.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 2:1"}, "These are the sons of Israel: Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 2:2"}, "Dan, Yusuf, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 2:3"}, "The sons of Judah: Er, Onan, and Shelah; which three were born to him of Shua\u2019s daughter the Canaanitess. Er, Judah\u2019s\nfirstborn, was wicked in the LORD\u2019s", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation\nof Allah\u2019s Proper Name."]}], "caller": "+"}, " sight; and he killed him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 2:4"}, "Tamar his daughter-in-law bore him Perez and Zerah. All the sons of Judah were five.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 2:5"}, "The sons of Perez: Hezron and Hamul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 2:6"}, "The sons of Zerah: Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Calcol, and Dara; five of them in all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 2:7"}, "The son of Carmi: Achar, the troubler of Israel, who committed a trespass in the devoted thing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 2:8"}, "The son of Ethan: Azariah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 2:9"}, "The sons also of Hezron, who were born to him: Jerahmeel, Ram, and Chelubai.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 2:10"}, "Ram became the father of Amminadab, and Amminadab became the father of Nahshon, prince of the children of Judah;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 2:11"}, "and Nahshon became the father of Salma, and Salma became the father of Boaz,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 2:12"}, "and Boaz became the father of Obed, and Obed became the father of Jesse;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 2:13"}, "and Jesse became the father of his firstborn Eliab, and Abinadab the second, and Shimea the third,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 2:14"}, "Nethanel the fourth, Raddai the fifth, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 2:15"}, "Ozem the sixth, Dawood the seventh; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 2:16"}, "and their sisters were Zeruiah and Abigail. The sons of Zeruiah: Abishai, Joab, and Asahel, three.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 2:17"}, "Abigail bore Amasa; and the father of Amasa was Jether the Ishmaelite.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 2:18"}, "Caleb the son of Hezron became the father of children of Azubah his wife, and of Jerioth; and these were her sons:\nJesher, Shobab, and Ardon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 2:19"}, "Azubah died, and Caleb married Ephrath, who bore him Hur. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 2:20"}, "Hur became the father of Uri, and Uri became the father of Bezalel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 2:21"}, "Afterward Hezron went in to the daughter of Machir the father of Gilead, whom he took as wife when he was sixty years\nold; and she bore him Segub. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 2:22"}, "Segub became the father of Jair, who had twenty-three cities in the land of Gilead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 2:23"}, "Geshur and Aram took the towns of Jair from them, with Kenath, and its villages, even sixty cities. All these were the\nsons of Machir the father of Gilead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 2:24"}, "After Hezron died in Caleb Ephrathah, Abijah Hezron\u2019s wife bore him Ashhur the father of Tekoa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 2:25"}, "The sons of Jerahmeel the firstborn of Hezron were Ram the firstborn, Bunah, Oren, Ozem, and Ahijah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 2:26"}, "Jerahmeel had another wife, whose name was Atarah. She was the mother of Onam.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 2:27"}, "The sons of Ram the firstborn of Jerahmeel were Maaz, Jamin, and Eker.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 2:28"}, "The sons of Onam were Shammai and Jada. The sons of Shammai: Nadab and Abishur.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 2:29"}, "The name of the wife of Abishur was Abihail; and she bore him Ahban and Molid.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 2:30"}, "The sons of Nadab: Seled and Appaim; but Seled died without children.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 2:31"}, "The son of Appaim: Ishi. The son of Ishi: Sheshan. The son of Sheshan: Ahlai.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 2:32"}, "The sons of Jada the brother of Shammai: Jether and Jonathan; and Jether died without children.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 2:33"}, "The sons of Jonathan: Peleth and Zaza. These were the sons of Jerahmeel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 2:34"}, "Now Sheshan had no sons, but daughters. Sheshan had a servant, an Egyptian, whose name was Jarha.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CH 2:35"}, "Sheshan gave his daughter to Jarha his servant as wife; and she bore him Attai.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CH 2:36"}, "Attai became the father of Nathan, and Nathan became the father of Zabad,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CH 2:37"}, "and Zabad became the father of Ephlal, and Ephlal became the father of Obed,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CH 2:38"}, "and Obed became the father of Jehu, and Jehu became the father of Azariah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CH 2:39"}, "and Azariah became the father of Helez, and Helez became the father of Eleasah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CH 2:40"}, "and Eleasah became the father of Sismai, and Sismai became the father of Shallum,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1CH 2:41"}, "and Shallum became the father of Jekamiah, and Jekamiah became the father of Elishama.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1CH 2:42"}, "The sons of Caleb the brother of Jerahmeel were Mesha his firstborn, who was the father of Ziph; and the sons of Mareshah\nthe father of Hebron. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1CH 2:43"}, "The sons of Hebron: Korah, Tappuah, Rekem, and Shema. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "1CH 2:44"}, "Shema became the father of Raham, the father of Jorkeam; and Rekem became the father of Shammai.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "1CH 2:45"}, "The son of Shammai was Maon; and Maon was the father of Beth Zur.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "1CH 2:46"}, "Ephah, Caleb\u2019s concubine, bore Haran, Moza, and Gazez; and Haran became the father of Gazez.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "1CH 2:47"}, "The sons of Jahdai: Regem, Jothan, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah, and Shaaph.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "1CH 2:48"}, "Maacah, Caleb\u2019s concubine, bore Sheber and Tirhanah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "1CH 2:49"}, "She bore also Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the father of Machbena, and the father of Gibea; and the daughter of\nCaleb was Achsah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "1CH 2:50"}, "These were the sons of Caleb, the son of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah: Shobal the father of Kiriath Jearim,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "1CH 2:51"}, "Salma the father of Bethlehem, and Hareph the father of Beth Gader.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "1CH 2:52"}, "Shobal the father of Kiriath Jearim had sons: Haroeh, half of the Menuhoth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "1CH 2:53"}, "The families of Kiriath Jearim: the Ithrites, the Puthites, the Shumathites, and the Mishraites; from them came the\nZorathites and the Eshtaolites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "1CH 2:54"}, "The sons of Salma: Bethlehem, the Netophathites, Atroth Beth Joab, and half of the Manahathites, the Zorites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "1CH 2:55"}, "The families of scribes who lived at Jabez: the Tirathites, the Shimeathites, and the Sucathites. These are the Kenites\nwho came from Hammath, the father of the house of Rechab. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 3:1"}, "Now these were the sons of Dawood, who were born to him in Hebron: the firstborn, Amnon, of Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; the\nsecond, Daniel, of Abigail the Carmelitess; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 3:2"}, "the third, Absalom the son of Maacah the daughter of Talmai king of Geshur; the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 3:3"}, "the fifth, Shephatiah of Abital; the sixth, Ithream by Eglah his wife:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 3:4"}, "six were born to him in Hebron; and he reigned there seven years and six months. He reigned thirty-three years in\nJerusalem; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 3:5"}, "and these were born to him in Jerusalem: Shimea, Shobab, Nathan, and Sulaiman, four, of Bathshua the daughter of Ammiel;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 3:6"}, "and Ibhar, Elishama, Eliphelet, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 3:7"}, "Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 3:8"}, "Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet, nine. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 3:9"}, "All these were the sons of Dawood, in addition to the sons of the concubines; and Tamar was their sister.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 3:10"}, "Sulaiman\u2019s son was Rehoboam, Abijah his son, Asa his son, Jehoshaphat his son,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 3:11"}, "Joram his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 3:12"}, "Amaziah his son, Azariah his son, Jotham his son, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 3:13"}, "Ahaz his son, Hezekiah his son, Manasseh his son, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 3:14"}, "Amon his son, and Josiah his son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 3:15"}, "The sons of Josiah: the firstborn Johanan, the second Jehoiakim, the third Zedekiah, and the fourth Shallum.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 3:16"}, "The sons of Jehoiakim: Jeconiah his son, and Zedekiah his son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 3:17"}, "The sons of Jeconiah, the captive: Shealtiel his son, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 3:18"}, "Malchiram, Pedaiah, Shenazzar, Jekamiah, Hoshama, and Nedabiah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 3:19"}, "The sons of Pedaiah: Zerubbabel and Shimei. The sons of Zerubbabel: Meshullam and Hananiah; and Shelomith was their\nsister; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 3:20"}, "and Hashubah, Ohel, Berechiah, Hasadiah, and Jushab Hesed, five.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 3:21"}, "The sons of Hananiah: Pelatiah and Jeshaiah; the sons of Rephaiah, the sons of Arnan, the sons of Obadiah, the sons of\nShecaniah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 3:22"}, "The son of Shecaniah: Shemaiah. The sons of Shemaiah: Hattush, Igal, Bariah, Neariah, and Shaphat, six.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 3:23"}, "The sons of Neariah: Elioenai, Hizkiah, and Azrikam, three.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 3:24"}, "The sons of Elioenai: Hodaviah, Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan, Delaiah, and Anani, seven.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 4:1"}, "The sons of Judah: Perez, Hezron, Carmi, Hur, and Shobal. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 4:2"}, "Reaiah the son of Shobal became the father of Jahath; and Jahath became the father of Ahumai and Lahad. These are the\nfamilies of the Zorathites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 4:3"}, "These were the sons of the father of Etam: Jezreel, Ishma, and Idbash. The name of their sister was Hazzelelponi.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 4:4"}, "Penuel was the father of Gedor and Ezer the father of Hushah. These are the sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah, the\nfather of Bethlehem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 4:5"}, "Ashhur the father of Tekoa had two wives, Helah and Naarah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 4:6"}, "Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni, and Haahashtari. These were the sons of Naarah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 4:7"}, "The sons of Helah were Zereth, Izhar, and Ethnan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 4:8"}, "Hakkoz became the father of Anub, Zobebah, and the families of Aharhel the son of Harum.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 4:9"}, "Jabez was more honourable than his brothers. His mother named him\nJabez,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cJabez\u201d sounds similar to the Hebrew word for\n\u201cpain\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " saying, \u201cBecause I bore him with sorrow.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 4:10"}, "Jabez called on Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d\n(Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of Israel, saying, \u201cOh that you would bless me indeed, and enlarge my border! May your hand be with me, and may\nyou keep me from evil, that I may not cause pain!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Allah granted him that which he requested. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 4:11"}, "Chelub the brother of Shuhah became the father of Mehir, who was the father of Eshton.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 4:12"}, "Eshton became the father of Beth Rapha, Paseah, and Tehinnah the father of Ir Nahash. These are the men of Recah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 4:13"}, "The sons of Kenaz: Othniel and Seraiah. The sons of Othniel: Hathath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 4:14"}, "Meonothai became the father of Ophrah: and Seraiah became the father of Joab the father of Ge Harashim; for they were\ncraftsmen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 4:15"}, "The sons of Caleb the son of Jephunneh: Iru, Elah, and Naam. The son of Elah: Kenaz.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 4:16"}, "The sons of Jehallelel: Ziph, Ziphah, Tiria, and Asarel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 4:17"}, "The sons of Ezrah: Jether, Mered, Epher, and Jalon; and she bore Miriam, Shammai, and Ishbah the father of Eshtemoa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 4:18"}, "His wife the Jewess bore Jered the father of Gedor, Heber the father of Soco, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah. These\nare the sons of Bithiah the daughter of Pharaoh, whom Mered took.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 4:19"}, "The sons of the wife of Hodiah, the sister of Naham, were the father of Keilah the Garmite, and Eshtemoa the Maacathite.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 4:20"}, "The sons of Shimon: Amnon, Rinnah, Ben Hanan, and Tilon. The sons of Ishi: Zoheth, and Ben Zoheth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 4:21"}, "The sons of Shelah the son of Judah: Er the father of Lecah, Laadah the father of Mareshah, and the families of the house\nof those who worked fine linen, of the house of Ashbea; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 4:22"}, "and Jokim, and the men of Cozeba, and Joash, and Saraph, who had dominion in Moab, and Jashubilehem. These records are\nancient. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 4:23"}, "These were the potters, and the inhabitants of Netaim and Gederah: they lived there with the king for his work.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 4:24"}, "The sons of Simeon: Nemuel, Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, Shaul; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 4:25"}, "Shallum his son, Mibsam his son, and Mishma his son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 4:26"}, "The sons of Mishma: Hammuel his son, Zaccur his son, Shimei his son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 4:27"}, "Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brothers didn\u2019t have many children, and all their family didn\u2019t\nmultiply like the children of Judah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 4:28"}, "They lived at Beersheba, Moladah, Hazarshual, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 4:29"}, "at Bilhah, at Ezem, at Tolad, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 4:30"}, "at Bethuel, at Hormah, at Ziklag, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 4:31"}, "at Beth Marcaboth, Hazar Susim, at Beth Biri, and at Shaaraim. These were their cities until Dawood\u2019s reign.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 4:32"}, "Their villages were Etam, Ain, Rimmon, Tochen, and Ashan, five cities;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 4:33"}, "and all their villages that were around the same cities, to Baal. These were their settlements, and they have their\ngenealogy. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 4:34"}, "Meshobab, Jamlech, Joshah the son of Amaziah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CH 4:35"}, "Joel, Jehu the son of Joshibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of Asiel,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CH 4:36"}, "Elioenai, Jaakobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adiel, Jesimiel, Benaiah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CH 4:37"}, "and Ziza the son of Shiphi, the son of Allon, the son of Jedaiah, the son of Shimri, the son of Shemaiah\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CH 4:38"}, "these mentioned by name were princes in their families. Their fathers\u2019 houses increased greatly.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CH 4:39"}, "They went to the entrance of Gedor, even to the east side of the valley, to seek pasture for their flocks.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CH 4:40"}, "They found fat pasture and good, and the land was wide, and quiet, and peaceful; for those who lived there before were\ndescended from Ham. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1CH 4:41"}, "These written by name came in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah, and struck their tents. The Meunim who were found\nthere, and they destroyed them utterly to this day, and lived in their place; because there was pasture there for their flocks.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1CH 4:42"}, "Some of them, even of the sons of Simeon, five hundred men, went to Mount Seir, having for their captains Pelatiah,\nNeariah, Rephaiah, and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1CH 4:43"}, "They struck the remnant of the Amalekites who escaped, and have lived there to this day.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 5:1"}, "The sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel (for he was the firstborn; but, because he defiled his father\u2019s couch, his\nbirthright was given to the sons of Yusuf the son of Israel; and the genealogy is not to be listed according to the birthright.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 5:2"}, "For Judah prevailed above his brothers, and from him came the prince; but the birthright was Yusuf\u2019s)\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 5:3"}, "the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel: Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 5:4"}, "The sons of Joel: Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 5:5"}, "Micah his son, Reaiah his son, Baal his son, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 5:6"}, "and Beerah his son, whom Tilgath Pilneser king of Assyria carried away captive. He was prince of the Reubenites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 5:7"}, "His brothers by their families, when the genealogy of their generations was listed: the chief, Jeiel, and Zakariya,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 5:8"}, "and Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel, who lived in Aroer, even to Nebo and Baal Meon;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 5:9"}, "and he lived eastward even to the entrance of the wilderness from the river Euphrates, because their livestock were\nmultiplied in the land of Gilead. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 5:10"}, "In the days of Saul, they made war with the Hagrites, who fell by their hand; and they lived in their tents throughout\nall the land east of Gilead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 5:11"}, "The sons of Gad lived beside them, in the land of Bashan to Salecah:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 5:12"}, "Joel the chief, Shapham the second, Janai, and Shaphat in Bashan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 5:13"}, "Their brothers of their fathers\u2019 houses: Michael, Meshullam, Sheba, Jorai, Jacan, Zia, and Eber, seven.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 5:14"}, "These were the sons of Abihail, the son of Huri, the son of Jaroah, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of\nJeshishai, the son of Jahdo, the son of Buz; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 5:15"}, "Ahi the son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, chief of their fathers\u2019 houses.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 5:16"}, "They lived in Gilead in Bashan, and in its towns, and in all the pasture lands of Sharon, as far as their borders.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 5:17"}, "All these were listed by genealogies in the days of Jotham king of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam king of Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 5:18"}, "The sons of Reuben, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, of valiant men, men able to bear buckler and sword, and\nto shoot with bow, and skilful in war, were forty-four thousand and seven hundred and sixty, that were able to go out to war.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 5:19"}, "They made war with the Hagrites, with Jetur, and Naphish, and Nodab.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 5:20"}, "They were helped against them, and the Hagrites were delivered into their hand, and all who were with them; for they\ncried to Allah in the battle, and he answered them, because they put their trust in him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 5:21"}, "They took away their livestock; of their camels fifty thousand, and of sheep two hundred and fifty thousand, and of\ndonkeys two thousand, and of men one hundred thousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 5:22"}, "For many fell slain, because the war was of Allah. They lived in their place until the captivity.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 5:23"}, "The children of the half-tribe of Manasseh lived in the land: they increased from Bashan to Baal Hermon, Senir, and Mount\nHermon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 5:24"}, "These were the heads of their fathers\u2019 houses: even Epher, Ishi, Eliel, Azriel, Jeremiah, Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, mighty\nmen of valour, famous men, heads of their fathers\u2019 houses. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 5:25"}, "They trespassed against Allah of their fathers, and played the prostitute after the gods of the peoples of the land, whom\nAllah destroyed before them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 5:26"}, "So Allah of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul king of Assyria, and the spirit of Tilgath Pilneser king of Assyria, and\nhe carried them away, even the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, and brought them to Halah, Habor,\nHara, and to the river of Gozan, to this day. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 6:1"}, "The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 6:2"}, "The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, and Hebron, and Uzziel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 6:3"}, "The children of Amram: Harun, Musa, and Miriam. The sons of Harun: Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 6:4"}, "Eleazar became the father of Phinehas, Phinehas became the father of Abishua,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 6:5"}, "Abishua became the father of Bukki. Bukki became the father of Uzzi.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 6:6"}, "Uzzi became the father of Zerahiah. Zerahiah became the father of Meraioth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 6:7"}, "Meraioth became the father of Amariah. Amariah became the father of Ahitub.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 6:8"}, "Ahitub became the father of Zadok. Zadok became the father of Ahimaaz.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 6:9"}, "Ahimaaz became the father of Azariah. Azariah became the father of Johanan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 6:10"}, "Johanan became the father of Azariah, who executed the priest\u2019s office in the house that Sulaiman built in Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 6:11"}, "Azariah became the father of Amariah. Amariah became the father of Ahitub.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 6:12"}, "Ahitub became the father of Zadok. Zadok became the father of Shallum.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 6:13"}, "Shallum became the father of Hilkiah. Hilkiah became the father of Azariah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 6:14"}, "Azariah became the father of Seraiah. Seraiah became the father of Jehozadak.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 6:15"}, "Jehozadak went into captivity, when the LORD carried Judah and Jerusalem away by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 6:16"}, "The sons of Levi: Gershom, Kohath, and Merari. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 6:17"}, "These are the names of the sons of Gershom: Libni and Shimei.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 6:18"}, "The sons of Kohath were Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 6:19"}, "The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. These are the families of the Levites according to their fathers\u2019 households.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 6:20"}, "Of Gershom: Libni his son, Jahath his son, Zimmah his son,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 6:21"}, "Joah his son, Iddo his son, Zerah his son, and Jeatherai his son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 6:22"}, "The sons of Kohath: Amminadab his son, Korah his son, Assir his son,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 6:23"}, "Elkanah his son, and Ebiasaph his son, Assir his son, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 6:24"}, "Tahath his son, Uriel his son, Uzziah his son, and Shaul his son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 6:25"}, "The sons of Elkanah: Amasai and Ahimoth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 6:26"}, "As for Elkanah, the sons of Elkanah: Zophai his son, Nahath his son,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 6:27"}, "Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, and Elkanah his son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 6:28"}, "The sons of Samuel: the firstborn, Joel, and the second, Abijah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 6:29"}, "The sons of Merari: Mahli, Libni his son, Shimei his son, Uzzah his son,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 6:30"}, "Shimea his son, Haggiah his son, Asaiah his son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 6:31"}, "These are they whom Dawood set over the service of song in the LORD\u2019s house, after the ark came to rest there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 6:32"}, "They ministered with song before the tabernacle of the Tent of Meeting, until Sulaiman had built the LORD\u2019s house in\nJerusalem. They performed the duties of their office according to their order.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 6:33"}, "These are those who served, and their sons. Of the sons of the Kohathites: Heman the singer, the son of Joel, the son of\nSamuel, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 6:34"}, "the son of Elkanah, the son of Jeroham, the son of Eliel, the son of Toah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CH 6:35"}, "the son of Zuph, the son of Elkanah, the son of Mahath, the son of Amasai,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CH 6:36"}, "the son of Elkanah, the son of Joel, the son of Azariah, the son of Zephaniah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CH 6:37"}, "the son of Tahath, the son of Assir, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CH 6:38"}, "the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, the son of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CH 6:39"}, "His brother Asaph, who stood on his right hand, even Asaph the son of Berechiah, the son of Shimea,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CH 6:40"}, "the son of Michael, the son of Baaseiah, the son of Malchijah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1CH 6:41"}, "the son of Ethni, the son of Zerah, the son of Adaiah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1CH 6:42"}, "the son of Ethan, the son of Zimmah, the son of Shimei, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1CH 6:43"}, "the son of Jahath, the son of Gershom, the son of Levi. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "1CH 6:44"}, "On the left hand their brothers the sons of Merari: Ethan the son of Kishi, the son of Abdi, the son of Malluch,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "1CH 6:45"}, "the son of Hashabiah, the son of Amaziah, the son of Hilkiah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "1CH 6:46"}, "the son of Amzi, the son of Bani, the son of Shemer, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "1CH 6:47"}, "the son of Mahli, the son of Mushi, the son of Merari, the son of Levi.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "1CH 6:48"}, "Their brothers the Levites were appointed for all the service of the tabernacle of Allah\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "1CH 6:49"}, "But Harun and his sons offered on the altar of burnt offering, and on the altar of incense, for all the work of the most\nholy place, and to make atonement for Israel, according to all that Musa the servant of Allah had commanded.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "1CH 6:50"}, "These are the sons of Harun: Eleazar his son, Phinehas his son, Abishua his son,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "1CH 6:51"}, "Bukki his son, Uzzi his son, Zerahiah his son, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "1CH 6:52"}, "Meraioth his son, Amariah his son, Ahitub his son, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "1CH 6:53"}, "Zadok his son, and Ahimaaz his son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "1CH 6:54"}, "Now these are their dwelling places according to their encampments in their borders: to the sons of Harun, of the\nfamilies of the Kohathites (for theirs was the first lot), \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "1CH 6:55"}, "to them they gave Hebron in the land of Judah, and its pasture lands around it;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "1CH 6:56"}, "but the fields of the city, and its villages, they gave to Caleb the son of Jephunneh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "1CH 6:57"}, "To the sons of Harun they gave the cities of refuge, Hebron; Libnah also with its pasture lands, Jattir, Eshtemoa with\nits pasture lands, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "1CH 6:58"}, "Hilen with its pasture lands, Debir with its pasture lands,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "59", "sid": "1CH 6:59"}, "Ashan with its pasture lands, and Beth Shemesh with its pasture lands;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "60", "sid": "1CH 6:60"}, "and out of the tribe of Benjamin, Geba with its pasture lands, Allemeth with its pasture lands, and Anathoth with its\npasture lands. All their cities throughout their families were thirteen cities.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "61", "sid": "1CH 6:61"}, "To the rest of the sons of Kohath were given by lot, out of the family of the tribe, out of the half-tribe, the half of\nManasseh, ten cities. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "62", "sid": "1CH 6:62"}, "To the sons of Gershom, according to their families, out of the tribe of Issachar, and out of the tribe of Asher, and out\nof the tribe of Naphtali, and out of the tribe of Manasseh in Bashan, thirteen cities.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "63", "sid": "1CH 6:63"}, "To the sons of Merari were given by lot, according to their families, out of the tribe of Reuben, and out of the tribe of\nGad, and out of the tribe of Zebulun, twelve cities. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "64", "sid": "1CH 6:64"}, "The children of Israel gave to the Levites the cities with their pasture lands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "65", "sid": "1CH 6:65"}, "They gave by lot out of the tribe of the children of Judah, and out of the tribe of the children of Simeon, and out of\nthe tribe of the children of Benjamin, these cities which are mentioned by name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "66", "sid": "1CH 6:66"}, "Some of the families of the sons of Kohath had cities of their borders out of the tribe of Ephraim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "67", "sid": "1CH 6:67"}, "They gave to them the cities of refuge, Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim with its pasture lands, and Gezer with its\npasture lands, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "68", "sid": "1CH 6:68"}, "Jokmeam with its pasture lands, Beth Horon with its pasture lands,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "69", "sid": "1CH 6:69"}, "Aijalon with its pasture lands, Gath Rimmon with its pasture lands;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "70", "sid": "1CH 6:70"}, "and out of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Aner with its pasture lands, and Bileam with its pasture lands, for the rest of\nthe family of the sons of Kohath. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "71", "sid": "1CH 6:71"}, "To the sons of Gershom were given, out of the family of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Golan in Bashan with its pasture\nlands, and Ashtaroth with its pasture lands; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "72", "sid": "1CH 6:72"}, "and out of the tribe of Issachar, Kedesh with its pasture lands, Daberath with its pasture lands,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "73", "sid": "1CH 6:73"}, "Ramoth with its pasture lands, and Anem with its pasture lands;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "74", "sid": "1CH 6:74"}, "and out of the tribe of Asher, Mashal with its pasture lands, Abdon with its pasture lands,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "75", "sid": "1CH 6:75"}, "Hukok with its pasture lands, and Rehob with its pasture lands;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "76", "sid": "1CH 6:76"}, "and out of the tribe of Naphtali, Kedesh in Galilee with its pasture lands, Hammon with its pasture lands, and Kiriathaim\nwith its pasture lands. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "77", "sid": "1CH 6:77"}, "To the rest of the Levites, the sons of Merari, were given, out of the tribe of Zebulun, Rimmono with its pasture lands,\nTabor with its pasture lands; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "78", "sid": "1CH 6:78"}, "and beyond the Jordan at Jericho, on the east side of the Jordan, were given them, out of the tribe of Reuben, Bezer in\nthe wilderness with its pasture lands, and Jahzah with its pasture lands,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "79", "sid": "1CH 6:79"}, "Kedemoth with its pasture lands, and Mephaath with its pasture lands;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "80", "sid": "1CH 6:80"}, "and out of the tribe of Gad, Ramoth in Gilead with its pasture lands, Mahanaim with its pasture lands,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "81", "sid": "1CH 6:81"}, "Heshbon with its pasture lands, and Jazer with its pasture lands.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 7:1"}, "Of the sons of Issachar: Tola, and Puah, Jashub, and Shimron, four.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 7:2"}, "The sons of Tola: Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeriel, Jahmai, Ibsam, and Shemuel, heads of their fathers\u2019 houses, of Tola; mighty men\nof valour in their generations. Their number in the days of Dawood was twenty-two thousand and six hundred.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 7:3"}, "The son of Uzzi: Izrahiah. The sons of Izrahiah: Michael, Obadiah, Joel, and Isshiah, five; all of them chief men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 7:4"}, "With them, by their generations, after their fathers\u2019 houses, were bands of the army for war, thirty-six thousand; for\nthey had many wives and sons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 7:5"}, "Their brothers amongst all the families of Issachar, mighty men of valour, listed in all by genealogy, were eighty-seven\nthousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 7:6"}, "The sons of Benjamin: Bela, Becher, and Jediael, three. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 7:7"}, "The sons of Bela: Ezbon, Uzzi, Uzziel, Jerimoth, and Iri, five; heads of fathers\u2019 houses, mighty men of valour; and they\nwere listed by genealogy twenty-two thousand and thirty-four. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 7:8"}, "The sons of Becher: Zemirah, Joash, Eliezer, Elioenai, Omri, Jeremoth, Abijah, Anathoth, and Alemeth. All these were the\nsons of Becher. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 7:9"}, "They were listed by genealogy, after their generations, heads of their fathers\u2019 houses, mighty men of valour, twenty\nthousand and two hundred. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 7:10"}, "The son of Jediael: Bilhan. The sons of Bilhan: Jeush, Benjamin, Ehud, Chenaanah, Zethan, Tarshish, and Ahishahar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 7:11"}, "All these were sons of Jediael, according to the heads of their fathers\u2019 households, mighty men of valour, seventeen\nthousand and two hundred, who were able to go out in the army for war.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 7:12"}, "So were Shuppim, Huppim, the sons of Ir, Hushim, and the sons of Aher.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 7:13"}, "The sons of Naphtali: Jahziel, Guni, Jezer, Shallum, and the sons of Bilhah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 7:14"}, "The sons of Manasseh: Asriel, whom his concubine the Aramitess bore. She bore Machir the father of Gilead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 7:15"}, "Machir took a wife of Huppim and Shuppim, whose sister\u2019s name was Maacah. The name of the second was Zelophehad; and\nZelophehad had daughters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 7:16"}, "Maacah the wife of Machir bore a son, and she named him Peresh. The name of his brother was Sheresh; and his sons were\nUlam and Rakem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 7:17"}, "The sons of Ulam: Bedan. These were the sons of Gilead the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 7:18"}, "His sister Hammolecheth bore Ishhod, Abiezer, and Mahlah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 7:19"}, "The sons of Shemida were Ahian, Shechem, Likhi, and Aniam.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 7:20"}, "The sons of Ephraim: Shuthelah, Bered his son, Tahath his son, Eleadah his son, Tahath his son,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 7:21"}, "Zabad his son, Shuthelah his son, Ezer, and Elead, whom the men of Gath who were born in the land killed, because they\ncame down to take away their livestock. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 7:22"}, "Ephraim their father mourned many days, and his brothers came to comfort him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 7:23"}, "He went in to his wife, and she conceived, and bore a son, and he named him\nBeriah,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBeriah\u201d is similar to the Hebrew word for\n\u201cmisfortune\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " because there was trouble with his house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 7:24"}, "His daughter was Sheerah, who built Beth Horon the lower and the upper, and Uzzen Sheerah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 7:25"}, "Rephah was his son, and Resheph, and Telah his son, Tahan his son,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 7:26"}, "Ladan his son, Ammihud his son, Elishama his son, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 7:27"}, "Nun his son, and Joshua his son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 7:28"}, "Their possessions and settlements were Bethel and its towns, and eastward Naaran, and westward Gezer, with its towns;\nShechem also and its towns, to Azzah and its towns; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 7:29"}, "and by the borders of the children of Manasseh, Beth Shean and its towns, Taanach and its towns, Megiddo and its towns,\nand Dor and its towns. The children of Yusuf the son of Israel lived in these.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 7:30"}, "The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, and Beriah. Serah was their sister.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 7:31"}, "The sons of Beriah: Heber and Malchiel, who was the father of Birzaith.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 7:32"}, "Heber became the father of Japhlet, Shomer, Hotham, and Shua their sister.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 7:33"}, "The sons of Japhlet: Pasach, Bimhal, and Ashvath. These are the children of Japhlet.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 7:34"}, "The sons of Shemer: Ahi, Rohgah, Jehubbah, and Aram. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CH 7:35"}, "The sons of Helem his brother: Zophah, Imna, Shelesh, and Amal.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CH 7:36"}, "The sons of Zophah: Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri, Imrah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CH 7:37"}, "Bezer, Hod, Shamma, Shilshah, Ithran, and Beera. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CH 7:38"}, "The sons of Jether: Jephunneh, Pispa, and Ara. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CH 7:39"}, "The sons of Ulla: Arah, Hanniel, and Rizia. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CH 7:40"}, "All these were the children of Asher, heads of the fathers\u2019 houses, choice and mighty men of valour, chief of the\nprinces. The number of them listed by genealogy for service in war was twenty-six thousand men.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 8:1"}, "Benjamin became the father of Bela his firstborn, Ashbel the second, Aharah the third,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 8:2"}, "Nohah the fourth, and Rapha the fifth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 8:3"}, "Bela had sons: Addar, Gera, Abihud, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 8:4"}, "Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 8:5"}, "Gera, Shephuphan, and Huram. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 8:6"}, "These are the sons of Ehud. These are the heads of fathers\u2019 households of the inhabitants of Geba, who were carried\ncaptive to Manahath: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 8:7"}, "Naaman, Ahijah, and Gera, who carried them captive; and he became the father of Uzza and Ahihud.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 8:8"}, "Shaharaim became the father of children in the field of Moab, after he had sent them away. Hushim and Baara were his\nwives. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 8:9"}, "By Hodesh his wife, he became the father of Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcam,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 8:10"}, "Jeuz, Shachia, and Mirmah. These were his sons, heads of fathers\u2019 households.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 8:11"}, "By Hushim, he became the father of Abitub and Elpaal. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 8:12"}, "The sons of Elpaal: Eber, Misham, and Shemed, who built Ono and Lod, with its towns;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 8:13"}, "and Beriah, and Shema, who were heads of fathers\u2019 households of the inhabitants of Aijalon, who put to flight the\ninhabitants of Gath; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 8:14"}, "and Ahio, Shashak, Jeremoth, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 8:15"}, "Zebadiah, Arad, Eder, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 8:16"}, "Michael, Ishpah, Joha, the sons of Beriah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 8:17"}, "Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 8:18"}, "Ishmerai, Izliah, Jobab, the sons of Elpaal, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 8:19"}, "Jakim, Zichri, Zabdi, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 8:20"}, "Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 8:21"}, "Adaiah, Beraiah, Shimrath, the sons of Shimei, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 8:22"}, "Ishpan, Eber, Eliel, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 8:23"}, "Abdon, Zichri, Hanan, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 8:24"}, "Hananiah, Elam, Anthothijah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 8:25"}, "Iphdeiah, Penuel, the sons of Shashak, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 8:26"}, "Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 8:27"}, "Jaareshiah, Ilyas, Zichri, and the sons of Jeroham. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 8:28"}, "These were heads of fathers\u2019 households throughout their generations, chief men. These lived in Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 8:29"}, "The father of Gibeon, whose wife\u2019s name was Maacah, lived in Gibeon,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 8:30"}, "with his firstborn son Abdon, Zur, Kish, Baal, Nadab, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 8:31"}, "Gedor, Ahio, and Zecher. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 8:32"}, "Mikloth became the father of Shimeah. They also lived with their brothers in Jerusalem, near their brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 8:33"}, "Ner became the father of Kish. Kish became the father of Saul. Saul became the father of Jonathan, Malchishua, Abinadab,\nand Eshbaal. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 8:34"}, "The son of Jonathan was Merib Baal. Merib Baal became the father of Micah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CH 8:35"}, "The sons of Micah: Pithon, Melech, Tarea, and Ahaz. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CH 8:36"}, "Ahaz became the father of Jehoaddah. Jehoaddah became the father of Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri. Zimri became the father\nof Moza. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CH 8:37"}, "Moza became the father of Binea. Raphah was his son, Eleasah his son, and Azel his son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CH 8:38"}, "Azel had six sons, whose names are these: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ismail, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. All these were the sons\nof Azel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CH 8:39"}, "The sons of Eshek his brother: Ulam his firstborn, Jeush the second, and Eliphelet the third.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CH 8:40"}, "The sons of Ulam were mighty men of valour, archers, and had many sons, and sons\u2019 sons, one hundred and fifty. All these\nwere of the sons of Benjamin. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 9:1"}, "So all Israel were listed by genealogies; and behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:1\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an\ninterjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " they are written in the book of the kings of Israel. Judah was carried away captive to Babylon for their\ndisobedience. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 9:2"}, "Now the first inhabitants who lived in their possessions in their cities were Israel, the priests, the Levites, and the\ntemple servants. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 9:3"}, "In Jerusalem lived of the children of Judah, of the children of Benjamin, and of the children of Ephraim and Manasseh:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 9:4"}, "Uthai the son of Ammihud, the son of Omri, the son of Imri, the son of Bani, of the children of Perez the son of Judah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 9:5"}, "Of the Shilonites: Asaiah the firstborn, and his sons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 9:6"}, "Of the sons of Zerah: Jeuel and their brothers, six hundred and ninety.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 9:7"}, "Of the sons of Benjamin: Sallu the son of Meshullam, the son of Hodaviah, the son of Hassenuah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 9:8"}, "and Ibneiah the son of Jeroham, and Elah the son of Uzzi, the son of Michri, and Meshullam the son of Shephatiah, the son\nof Reuel, the son of Ibnijah; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 9:9"}, "and their brothers, according to their generations, nine hundred and fifty-six. All these men were heads of fathers\u2019\nhouseholds by their fathers\u2019 houses. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 9:10"}, "Of the priests: Jedaiah, Jehoiarib, Jachin, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 9:11"}, "and Azariah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, the ruler\nof Allah\u2019s house; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 9:12"}, "and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pashhur, the son of Malchijah, and Maasai the son of Adiel, the son of\nJahzerah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Meshillemith, the son of Immer;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 9:13"}, "and their brothers, heads of their fathers\u2019 houses, one thousand and seven hundred and sixty; very able men for the work\nof the service of Allah\u2019s house. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 9:14"}, "Of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam, the son of Hashabiah, of the sons of Merari;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 9:15"}, "and Bakbakkar, Heresh, Galal, and Mattaniah the son of Mica, the son of Zichri, the son of Asaph,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 9:16"}, "and Obadiah the son of Shemaiah, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun, and Berechiah the son of Asa, the son of Elkanah,\nwho lived in the villages of the Netophathites. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 9:17"}, "The gatekeepers: Shallum, Akkub, Talmon, Ahiman, and their brothers (Shallum was the chief),\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 9:18"}, "who previously served in the king\u2019s gate eastward. They were the gatekeepers for the camp of the children of Levi.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 9:19"}, "Shallum the son of Kore, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah, and his brothers, of his father\u2019s house, the Korahites,\nwere over the work of the service, keepers of the thresholds of the tent. Their fathers had been over the LORD\u2019s camp, keepers\nof the entry. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 9:20"}, "Phinehas the son of Eleazar was ruler over them in time past, and the LORD was with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 9:21"}, "Zakariya the son of Meshelemiah was gatekeeper of the door of the Tent of Meeting.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 9:22"}, "All these who were chosen to be gatekeepers in the thresholds were two hundred and twelve. These were listed by genealogy\nin their villages, whom Dawood and Samuel the seer ordained in their office of trust.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 9:23"}, "So they and their children had the oversight of the gates of the LORD\u2019s house, even the house of the tent, as guards.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 9:24"}, "On the four sides were the gatekeepers, towards the east, west, north, and south.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 9:25"}, "Their brothers, in their villages, were to come in every seven days from time to time to be with them:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 9:26"}, "for the four chief gatekeepers, who were Levites, were in an office of trust, and were over the rooms and over the\ntreasuries in Allah\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 9:27"}, "They stayed around Allah\u2019s house, because that duty was on them; and to their duty was its opening morning by morning.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 9:28"}, "Certain of them were in charge of the vessels of service; for these were brought in by count, and these were taken out by\ncount. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 9:29"}, "Some of them also were appointed over the furniture, and over all the vessels of the sanctuary, over the fine flour, the\nwine, the oil, the frankincense, and the spices. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 9:30"}, "Some of the sons of the priests prepared the mixing of the spices.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 9:31"}, "Mattithiah, one of the Levites, who was the firstborn of Shallum the Korahite, had the office of trust over the things\nthat were baked in pans. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 9:32"}, "Some of their brothers, of the sons of the Kohathites, were over the show bread, to prepare it every Sabbath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 9:33"}, "These are the singers, heads of fathers\u2019 households of the Levites, who lived in the rooms and were free from other\nservice; for they were employed in their work day and night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 9:34"}, "These were heads of fathers\u2019 households of the Levites, throughout their generations, chief men. These lived at\nJerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CH 9:35"}, "Jeiel the father of Gibeon, whose wife\u2019s name was Maacah, lived in Gibeon with\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CH 9:36"}, "his firstborn son Abdon, Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CH 9:37"}, "Gedor, Ahio, Zakariya, and Mikloth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CH 9:38"}, "Mikloth became the father of Shimeam. They also lived with their brothers in Jerusalem, near their brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CH 9:39"}, "Ner became the father of Kish. Kish became the father of Saul. Saul became the father of Jonathan, Malchishua, Abinadab,\nand Eshbaal. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CH 9:40"}, "The son of Jonathan was Merib Baal. Merib Baal became the father of Micah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1CH 9:41"}, "The sons of Micah: Pithon, Melech, Tahrea, and Ahaz. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1CH 9:42"}, "Ahaz became the father of Jarah. Jarah became the father of Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri. Zimri became the father of\nMoza. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1CH 9:43"}, "Moza became the father of Binea; and Rephaiah his son, Eleasah his son, and Azel his son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "1CH 9:44"}, "Azel had six sons, whose names are these: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ismail, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. These were the sons of\nAzel. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 10:1"}, "Now the Philistines fought against Israel, and the men of Israel fled from before the Philistines, and fell down slain on\nMount Gilboa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 10:2"}, "The Philistines followed hard after Saul and after his sons; and the Philistines killed Jonathan, Abinadab, and\nMalchishua, the sons of Saul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 10:3"}, "The battle went hard against Saul, and the archers overtook him; and he was distressed by reason of the archers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 10:4"}, "Then Saul said to his armour bearer, \u201cDraw your sword, and thrust me through with it, lest these uncircumcised come and\nabuse me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But his armour bearer would not; for he was terrified. Therefore Saul took his sword, and fell on it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 10:5"}, "When his armour bearer saw that Saul was dead, he likewise fell on his sword, and died.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 10:6"}, "So Saul died with his three sons; and all his house died together.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 10:7"}, "When all the men of Israel who were in the valley saw that they fled, and that Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned\ntheir cities, and fled; and the Philistines came and lived in them.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 10:8"}, "On the next day, when the Philistines came to strip the slain, they found Saul and his sons fallen on Mount Gilboa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 10:9"}, "They stripped him, and took his head and his armour, and sent into the land of the Philistines all around, to carry the\nnews to their idols, and to the people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 10:10"}, "They put his armour in the house of their gods, and fastened his head in the house of Dagon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 10:11"}, "When all Jabesh Gilead heard all that the Philistines had done to Saul,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 10:12"}, "all the valiant men arose, and took away the body of Saul, and the bodies of his sons, and brought them to Jabesh, and\nburied their bones under the oak in Jabesh, and fasted seven days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 10:13"}, "So Saul died for his trespass which he committed against the LORD, because of the LORD\u2019s word, which he didn\u2019t keep; and\nalso because he asked counsel of one who had a familiar spirit, to enquire,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 10:14"}, "and didn\u2019t enquire of the LORD. Therefore he killed him, and turned the kingdom over to Dawood the son of Jesse.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 11:1"}, "Then all Israel gathered themselves to Dawood to Hebron, saying, \u201cBehold, we are your bone and your flesh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 11:2"}, "In times past, even when Saul was king, it was you who led out and brought in Israel. The LORD your Allah said to you,\n\u2018You shall be shepherd of my people Israel, and you shall be prince over my people Israel.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 11:3"}, "So all the elders of Israel came to the king to Hebron; and Dawood made a covenant with them in Hebron before the LORD;\nand they anointed Dawood king over Israel, according to the LORD\u2019s word by Samuel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 11:4"}, "Dawood and all Israel went to Jerusalem (also called Jebus); and the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land, were there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 11:5"}, "The inhabitants of Jebus said to Dawood, \u201cYou will not come in here.\u201d Nevertheless Dawood took the stronghold of Zion. The\nsame is Dawood\u2019s city. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 11:6"}, "Dawood said, \u201cWhoever strikes the Jebusites first shall be chief and captain.\u201d Joab the son of Zeruiah went up first, and\nwas made chief. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 11:7"}, "Dawood lived in the stronghold; therefore they called it Dawood\u2019s city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 11:8"}, "He built the city all around, from Millo even around; and Joab repaired the rest of the city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 11:9"}, "Dawood grew greater and greater; for the LORD of Armies was with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 11:10"}, "Now these are the chief of the mighty men whom Dawood had, who showed themselves strong with him in his kingdom, together\nwith all Israel, to make him king, according to the LORD\u2019s word concerning Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 11:11"}, "This is the number of the mighty men whom Dawood had: Jashobeam, the son of a Hachmonite, the chief of the thirty; he\nlifted up his spear against three hundred and killed them at one time.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 11:12"}, "After him was Eleazar the son of Dodo, the Ahohite, who was one of the three mighty men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 11:13"}, "He was with Dawood at Pasdammim, and there the Philistines were gathered together to battle, where there was a plot of\nground full of barley; and the people fled from before the Philistines.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 11:14"}, "They stood in the middle of the plot, defended it, and killed the Philistines; and the LORD saved them by a great\nvictory. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 11:15"}, "Three of the thirty chief men went down to the rock to Dawood, into the cave of Adullam; and the army of the Philistines\nwere encamped in the valley of Rephaim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 11:16"}, "Dawood was then in the stronghold, and the garrison of the Philistines was in Bethlehem at that time.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 11:17"}, "Dawood longed, and said, \u201cOh that one would give me water to drink from the well of Bethlehem, which is by the gate!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 11:18"}, "The three broke through the army of the Philistines, and drew water out of the well of Bethlehem, that was by the gate,\nand took it, and brought it to Dawood; but Dawood would not drink any of it, but poured it out to the LORD,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 11:19"}, "and said, \u201cMy Allah forbid me, that I should do this! Shall I drink the blood of these men who have put their lives in\njeopardy?\u201d For they risked their lives to bring it. Therefore he would not drink it. The three mighty men did these things.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 11:20"}, "Abishai, the brother of Joab, he was chief of the three; for he lifted up his spear against three hundred and killed\nthem, and had a name amongst the three. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 11:21"}, "Of the three, he was more honourable than the two, and was made their captain; however he wasn\u2019t included in the three.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 11:22"}, "Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man of Kabzeel, who had done mighty deeds, killed the two sons of Ariel\nof Moab. He also went down and killed a lion in the middle of a pit on a snowy day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 11:23"}, "He killed an Egyptian, a man of great stature, five cubits", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man\u2019s arm, or about 18 inches or 46\ncentimetres. Therefore this Egyptian was bout 7 feet and 6 inches or 2.28 metres\ntall."]}], "caller": "+"}, " high. In the Egyptian\u2019s hand was a spear like a weaver\u2019s beam; and he went down to him with a staff, plucked the spear\nout of the Egyptian\u2019s hand, and killed him with his own spear. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 11:24"}, "Benaiah the son of Jehoiada did these things, and had a name amongst the three mighty men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 11:25"}, "Behold, he was more honourable than the thirty, but he didn\u2019t attain to the three; and Dawood set him over his guard.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 11:26"}, "The mighty men of the armies also include Asahel the brother of Joab, Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 11:27"}, "Shammoth the Harorite, Helez the Pelonite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 11:28"}, "Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite, Abiezer the Anathothite,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 11:29"}, "Sibbecai the Hushathite, Ilai the Ahohite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 11:30"}, "Maharai the Netophathite, Heled the son of Baanah the Netophathite,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 11:31"}, "Ithai the son of Ribai of Gibeah of the children of Benjamin, Benaiah the Pirathonite,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 11:32"}, "Hurai of the brooks of Gaash, Abiel the Arbathite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 11:33"}, "Azmaveth the Baharumite, Eliahba the Shaalbonite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 11:34"}, "the sons of Hashem the Gizonite, Jonathan the son of Shagee the Hararite,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CH 11:35"}, "Ahiam the son of Sacar the Hararite, Eliphal the son of Ur,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CH 11:36"}, "Hepher the Mecherathite, Ahijah the Pelonite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CH 11:37"}, "Hezro the Carmelite, Naarai the son of Ezbai, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CH 11:38"}, "Joel the brother of Nathan, Mibhar the son of Hagri, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CH 11:39"}, "Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Berothite, the armour bearer of Joab the son of Zeruiah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CH 11:40"}, "Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1CH 11:41"}, "Uriah the Hittite, Zabad the son of Ahlai, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1CH 11:42"}, "Adina the son of Shiza the Reubenite, a chief of the Reubenites, and thirty with him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1CH 11:43"}, "Hanan the son of Maacah, and Joshaphat the Mithnite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "1CH 11:44"}, "Uzzia the Ashterathite, Shama and Jeiel the sons of Hotham the Aroerite,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "1CH 11:45"}, "Jediael the son of Shimri, and Joha his brother, the Tizite,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "1CH 11:46"}, "Eliel the Mahavite, and Jeribai, and Joshaviah, the sons of Elnaam, and Ithmah the Moabite,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "1CH 11:47"}, "Eliel, and Obed, and Jaasiel the Mezobaite. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 12:1"}, "Now these are those who came to Dawood to Ziklag, while he was a fugitive from Saul the son of Kish. They were amongst the\nmighty men, his helpers in war. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 12:2"}, "They were armed with bows, and could use both the right hand and the left in slinging stones and in shooting arrows from\nthe bow. They were of Saul\u2019s relatives of the tribe of Benjamin.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 12:3"}, "The chief was Ahiezer, then Joash, the sons of Shemaah the Gibeathite; Jeziel and Pelet, the sons of Azmaveth; Beracah;\nJehu the Anathothite; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 12:4"}, "Ishmaiah the Gibeonite, a mighty man amongst the thirty and a leader of the thirty; Jeremiah; Jahaziel; Johanan; Jozabad\nthe Gederathite; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 12:5"}, "Eluzai; Jerimoth; Bealiah; Shemariah; Shephatiah the Haruphite;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 12:6"}, "Elkanah, Isshiah Azarel, Joezer, and Jashobeam, the Korahites;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 12:7"}, "and Joelah and Zebadiah, the sons of Jeroham of Gedor. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 12:8"}, "Some Gadites joined Dawood in the stronghold in the wilderness, mighty men of valour, men trained for war, who could\nhandle shield and spear; whose faces were like the faces of lions, and they were as swift as the gazelles on the mountains:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 12:9"}, "Ezer the chief, Obadiah the second, Eliab the third, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 12:10"}, "Mishmannah the fourth, Jeremiah the fifth, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 12:11"}, "Attai the sixth, Eliel the seventh, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 12:12"}, "Johanan the eighth, Elzabad the ninth, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 12:13"}, "Jeremiah the tenth, and Machbannai the eleventh. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 12:14"}, "These of the sons of Gad were captains of the army: he who was least was equal to one hundred, and the greatest to one\nthousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 12:15"}, "These are those who went over the Jordan in the first month, when it had overflowed all its banks; and they put to flight\nall who lived in the valleys, both towards the east and towards the west.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 12:16"}, "Some of the children of Benjamin and Judah came to the stronghold to Dawood.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 12:17"}, "Dawood went out to meet them, and answered them, \u201cIf you have come peaceably to me to help me, my heart will be united\nwith you; but if you have come to betray me to my adversaries, since there is no wrong in my hands, may Allah of our fathers\nsee this and rebuke it.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 12:18"}, "Then the Spirit came on Amasai, who was chief of the thirty, and he said, \u201cWe are yours, Dawood, and on your side, you\nson of Jesse. Peace, peace be to you, and peace be to your helpers; for your Allah helps you.\u201d Then Dawood received them, and\nmade them captains of the band. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 12:19"}, "Some of Manasseh also joined Dawood, when he came with the Philistines against Saul to battle; but they didn\u2019t help them;\nfor the lords of the Philistines sent him away after consultation, saying, \u201cHe will desert to his master Saul to the jeopardy\nof our heads.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 12:20"}, "As he went to Ziklag, some from Manasseh joined him: Adnah, Jozabad, Jediael, Michael, Jozabad, Elihu, and Zillethai,\ncaptains of thousands who were of Manasseh. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 12:21"}, "They helped Dawood against the band of rovers; for they were all mighty men of valour, and were captains in the army.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 12:22"}, "For from day to day men came to Dawood to help him, until there was a great army, like Allah\u2019s army.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 12:23"}, "These are the numbers of the heads of those who were armed for war, who came to Dawood to Hebron, to turn the kingdom of\nSaul to him, according to the LORD\u2019s word. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 12:24"}, "The children of Judah who bore shield and spear were six thousand and eight hundred, armed for war.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 12:25"}, "Of the children of Simeon, mighty men of valour for the war: seven thousand and one hundred.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 12:26"}, "Of the children of Levi: four thousand and six hundred. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 12:27"}, "Jehoiada was the leader of the household of Harun; and with him were three thousand and seven hundred,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 12:28"}, "and Zadok, a young man mighty of valour, and of his father\u2019s house twenty-two captains.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 12:29"}, "Of the children of Benjamin, Saul\u2019s relatives: three thousand, for until then, the greatest part of them had kept their\nallegiance to Saul\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 12:30"}, "Of the children of Ephraim: twenty thousand and eight hundred, mighty men of valour, famous men in their fathers\u2019 houses.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 12:31"}, "Of the half-tribe of Manasseh: eighteen thousand, who were mentioned by name, to come and make Dawood king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 12:32"}, "Of the children of Issachar, men who had understanding of the times, to know what Israel ought to do, their heads were\ntwo hundred; and all their brothers were at their command. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 12:33"}, "Of Zebulun, such as were able to go out in the army, who could set the battle in array, with all kinds of instruments of\nwar: fifty thousand who could command and were not of double heart.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 12:34"}, "Of Naphtali: one thousand captains, and with them with shield and spear thirty-seven thousand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CH 12:35"}, "Of the Danites who could set the battle in array: twenty-eight thousand and six hundred.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CH 12:36"}, "Of Asher, such as were able to go out in the army, who could set the battle in array: forty thousand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CH 12:37"}, "On the other side of the Jordan, of the Reubenites, the Gadites, and of the half-tribe of Manasseh, with all kinds of\ninstruments of war for the battle: one hundred and twenty thousand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CH 12:38"}, "All these were men of war, who could order the battle array, and came with a perfect heart to Hebron, to make Dawood king\nover all Israel; and all the rest also of Israel were of one heart to make Dawood king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CH 12:39"}, "They were there with Dawood three days, eating and drinking; for their brothers had supplied provisions for them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CH 12:40"}, "Moreover those who were near to them, as far as Issachar, Zebulun, and Naphtali, brought bread on donkeys, on camels, on\nmules, and on oxen: supplies of flour, cakes of figs, clusters of raisins, wine, oil, cattle, and sheep in abundance; for there\nwas joy in Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 13:1"}, "Dawood consulted with the captains of thousands and of hundreds, even with every leader.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 13:2"}, "Dawood said to all the assembly of Israel, \u201cIf it seems good to you, and if it is of the LORD our Allah, let\u2019s send word\neverywhere to our brothers who are left in all the land of Israel, with whom the priests and Levites are in their cities that\nhave pasture lands, that they may gather themselves to us. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 13:3"}, "Also, let\u2019s bring the ark of our Allah back to us again; for we didn\u2019t seek it in the days of Saul.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 13:4"}, "All the assembly said that they would do so; for the thing was right in the eyes of all the people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 13:5"}, "So Dawood assembled all Israel together, from the Shihor the brook of Egypt even to the entrance of Hamath, to bring\nAllah\u2019s ark from Kiriath Jearim. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 13:6"}, "Dawood went up with all Israel to Baalah, that is, to Kiriath Jearim, which belonged to Judah, to bring up from there\nAllah the LORD\u2019s ark that sits above the cherubim, that is called by the Name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 13:7"}, "They carried Allah\u2019s ark on a new cart, and brought it out of Abinadab\u2019s house; and Uzza and Ahio drove the cart.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 13:8"}, "Dawood and all Israel played before Allah with all their might, even with songs, with harps, with stringed instruments,\nwith tambourines, with cymbals, and with trumpets. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 13:9"}, "When they came to Chidon\u2019s threshing floor, Uzza put out his hand to hold the ark; for the oxen stumbled.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 13:10"}, "The LORD\u2019s anger burnt against Uzza, and he struck him, because he put his hand on the ark; and he died there before\nAllah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 13:11"}, "Dawood was displeased, because the LORD had broken out against Uzza. He called that place Perez Uzza, to this day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 13:12"}, "Dawood was afraid of Allah that day, saying, \u201cHow can I bring Allah\u2019s ark home to me?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 13:13"}, "So Dawood didn\u2019t move the ark with him into Dawood\u2019s city, but carried it aside into Obed-Edom the Gittite\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 13:14"}, "Allah\u2019s ark remained with the family of Obed-Edom in his house three months; and the LORD blessed Obed-Edom\u2019s house and\nall that he had. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 14:1"}, "Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to Dawood with cedar trees, masons, and carpenters, to build him a house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 14:2"}, "Dawood perceived that the LORD had established him king over Israel; for his kingdom was exalted on high, for his people\nIsrael\u2019s sake. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 14:3"}, "Dawood took more wives at Jerusalem, and Dawood became the father of more sons and daughters.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 14:4"}, "These are the names of the children whom he had in Jerusalem: Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Sulaiman,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 14:5"}, "Ibhar, Elishua, Elpelet, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 14:6"}, "Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 14:7"}, "Elishama, Beeliada, and Eliphelet. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 14:8"}, "When the Philistines heard that Dawood was anointed king over all Israel, all the Philistines went up to seek Dawood; and\nDawood heard of it, and went out against them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 14:9"}, "Now the Philistines had come and made a raid in the valley of Rephaim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 14:10"}, "Dawood enquired of Allah, saying, \u201cShall I go up against the Philistines? Will you deliver them into my hand?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD said to him, \u201cGo up; for I will deliver them into your hand.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 14:11"}, "So they came up to Baal Perazim, and Dawood defeated them there. Dawood said, Allah has broken my enemies by my hand,\nlike waters breaking out. Therefore they called the name of that place Baal\nPerazim.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBaal Perazim\u201d means \u201cThe Lord who breaks\nout\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 14:12"}, "They left their gods there; and Dawood gave a command, and they were burnt with fire.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 14:13"}, "The Philistines made a another raid in the valley. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 14:14"}, "Dawood enquired again of Allah; and Allah said to him, \u201cYou shall not go up after them. Turn away from them, and come on\nthem opposite the mulberry trees. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 14:15"}, "When you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the mulberry trees, then go out to battle; for Allah has gone out\nbefore you to strike the army of the Philistines.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 14:16"}, "Dawood did as Allah commanded him; and they attacked the army of the Philistines from Gibeon even to Gezer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 14:17"}, "The fame of Dawood went out into all lands; and the LORD brought the fear of him on all nations.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 15:1"}, "Dawood made himself houses in Dawood\u2019s city; and he prepared a place for Allah\u2019s ark, and pitched a tent for it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 15:2"}, "Then Dawood said, \u201cNo one ought to carry Allah\u2019s ark but the Levites. For the LORD has chosen them to carry Allah\u2019s ark,\nand to minister to him forever.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 15:3"}, "Dawood assembled all Israel at Jerusalem, to bring up the LORD\u2019s ark to its place, which he had prepared for it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 15:4"}, "Dawood gathered together the sons of Harun and the Levites:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 15:5"}, "of the sons of Kohath, Uriel the chief, and his brothers one hundred and twenty;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 15:6"}, "of the sons of Merari, Asaiah the chief, and his brothers two hundred and twenty;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 15:7"}, "of the sons of Gershom, Joel the chief, and his brothers one hundred and thirty;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 15:8"}, "of the sons of Elizaphan, Shemaiah the chief, and his brothers two hundred;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 15:9"}, "of the sons of Hebron, Eliel the chief, and his brothers eighty;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 15:10"}, "of the sons of Uzziel, Amminadab the chief, and his brothers one hundred and twelve.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 15:11"}, "Dawood called for Zadok and Abiathar the priests, and for the Levites, for Uriel, Asaiah, Joel, Shemaiah, Eliel, and\nAmminadab, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 15:12"}, "and said to them, \u201cYou are the heads of the fathers\u2019 households of the Levites. Sanctify yourselves, both you and your\nbrothers, that you may bring the ark of the LORD, Allah of Israel, up to the place that I have prepared for it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 15:13"}, "For because you didn\u2019t carry it at first, the LORD our Allah broke out in anger against us, because we didn\u2019t seek him\naccording to the ordinance.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 15:14"}, "So the priests and the Levites sanctified themselves to bring up the ark of the LORD, Allah of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 15:15"}, "The children of the Levites bore Allah\u2019s ark on their shoulders with its poles, as Musa commanded according to the LORD\u2019s\nword. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 15:16"}, "Dawood spoke to the chief of the Levites to appoint their brothers as singers with instruments of music, stringed\ninstruments, harps, and cymbals, sounding aloud and lifting up their voices with joy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 15:17"}, "So the Levites appointed Heman the son of Joel; and of his brothers, Asaph the son of Berechiah; and of the sons of\nMerari their brothers, Ethan the son of Kushaiah; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 15:18"}, "and with them their brothers of the second rank, Zakariya, Ben, Jaaziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Benaiah,\nMaaseiah, Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, Obed-Edom, and Jeiel, the doorkeepers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 15:19"}, "So the singers, Heman, Asaph, and Ethan, were given cymbals of bronze to sound aloud;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 15:20"}, "and Zakariya, Aziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah, and Benaiah, with stringed instruments set to Alamoth;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 15:21"}, "and Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, Obed-Edom, Jeiel, and Azaziah, with harps tuned to the eight-stringed lyre, to\nlead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 15:22"}, "Chenaniah, chief of the Levites, was over the singing. He taught the singers, because he was skilful.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 15:23"}, "Berechiah and Elkanah were doorkeepers for the ark. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 15:24"}, "Shebaniah, Joshaphat, Nethanel, Amasai, Zakariya, Benaiah, and Eliezer, the priests, blew the trumpets before Allah\u2019s\nark; and Obed-Edom and Jehiah were doorkeepers for the ark. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 15:25"}, "So Dawood, the elders of Israel, and the captains over thousands, went to bring the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant up out of\nthe house of Obed-Edom with joy. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 15:26"}, "When Allah helped the Levites who bore the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant, they sacrificed seven bulls and seven rams.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 15:27"}, "Dawood was clothed with a robe of fine linen, as were all the Levites who bore the ark, the singers, and Chenaniah the\nchoir master with the singers; and Dawood had an ephod of linen on him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 15:28"}, "Thus all Israel brought the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant up with shouting, with sound of the cornet, with trumpets, and\nwith cymbals, sounding aloud with stringed instruments and harps.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 15:29"}, "As the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant came to Dawood\u2019s city, Michal the daughter of Saul looked out at the window, and saw\nking Dawood dancing and playing; and she despised him in her heart.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 16:1"}, "They brought in Allah\u2019s ark, and set it in the middle of the tent that Dawood had pitched for it; and they offered burnt\nofferings and peace offerings before Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 16:2"}, "When Dawood had finished offering the burnt offering and the peace offerings, he blessed the people in the LORD\u2019s name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 16:3"}, "He gave to everyone of Israel, both man and woman, to everyone a loaf of bread, a portion of meat, and a cake of raisins.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 16:4"}, "He appointed some of the Levites to minister before the LORD\u2019s ark, and to commemorate, to thank, and to praise the LORD,\nAllah of Israel: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 16:5"}, "Asaph the chief, and second to him Zakariya, then Jeiel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab, Benaiah, Obed-Edom, and\nJeiel, with stringed instruments and with harps; and Asaph with cymbals, sounding aloud;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 16:6"}, "with Benaiah and Jahaziel the priests with trumpets continually, before the ark of the covenant of Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 16:7"}, "Then on that day Dawood first ordained to give thanks to the LORD, by the hand of Asaph and his brothers.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 16:8"}, "Oh give thanks to the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Call on his name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Make what he has done known amongst the peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 16:9"}, "Sing to him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Sing praises to him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Tell of all his marvellous works. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 16:10"}, "Glory in his holy name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let the heart of those who seek the LORD rejoice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 16:11"}, "Seek the LORD and his strength. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Seek his face forever more. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 16:12"}, "Remember his marvellous works that he has done, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["his wonders, and the judgements of his mouth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 16:13"}, "you offspring", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of Israel his servant,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you children of Yaqub, his chosen ones. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 16:14"}, "He is the LORD our Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His judgements are in all the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 16:15"}, "Remember his covenant forever, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the word which he commanded to a thousand generations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 16:16"}, "the covenant which he made with Ibrahim, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["his oath to Is\u1e25\u0101q. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 16:17"}, "He confirmed it to Yaqub for a statute, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to Israel for an everlasting covenant, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 16:18"}, "saying, \u201cI will give you the land of Canaan, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The lot of your inheritance,\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 16:19"}, "when you were but a few men in number, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, very few, and foreigners were in it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 16:20"}, "They went about from nation to nation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from one kingdom to another people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 16:21"}, "He allowed no man to do them wrong. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, he reproved kings for their sakes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 16:22"}, "\u201cDon\u2019t touch my anointed ones! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Do my prophets no harm!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 16:23"}, "Sing to the LORD, all the earth! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Display his salvation from day to day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 16:24"}, "Declare his glory amongst the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his marvellous works amongst all the peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 16:25"}, "For great is the LORD, and greatly to be praised. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He also is to be feared above all gods. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 16:26"}, "For all the gods of the peoples are idols, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but the LORD made the heavens. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 16:27"}, "Honour and majesty are before him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Strength and gladness are in his place. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 16:28"}, "Ascribe to the LORD, you relatives of the peoples, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["ascribe to the LORD glory and strength! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 16:29"}, "Ascribe to the LORD the glory due to his name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Bring an offering, and come before him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Worship the LORD in holy array. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 16:30"}, "Tremble before him, all the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The world also is established that it can\u2019t be moved. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 16:31"}, "Let the heavens be glad, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and let the earth rejoice! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let them say amongst the nations, \u201cThe LORD reigns!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 16:32"}, "Let the sea roar, and its fullness! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let the field exult, and all that is in it! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 16:33"}, "Then the trees of the forest will sing for joy before the LORD,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for he comes to judge the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 16:34"}, "Oh give thanks to the LORD, for he is good, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for his loving kindness endures forever. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CH 16:35"}, "Say, \u201cSave us, Allah of our salvation! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Gather us together and deliver us from the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to give thanks to your holy name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to triumph in your praise.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CH 16:36"}, "Blessed be the LORD, Allah of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from everlasting even to everlasting. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people said, \u201cAmen,\u201d and praised the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CH 16:37"}, "So he left Asaph and his brothers there before the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant, to minister before the ark continually, as\nevery day\u2019s work required; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CH 16:38"}, "and Obed-Edom with their brothers, sixty-eight; Obed-Edom also the son of Jeduthun and Hosah to be doorkeepers;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CH 16:39"}, "and Zadok the priest, and his brothers the priests, before the LORD\u2019s tabernacle in the high place that was at Gibeon,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CH 16:40"}, "to offer burnt offerings to the LORD on the altar of burnt offering continually morning and evening, even according to\nall that is written in the LORD\u2019s law, which he commanded to Israel;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1CH 16:41"}, "and with them Heman and Jeduthun, and the rest who were chosen, who were mentioned by name, to give thanks to the LORD,\nbecause his loving kindness endures forever; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1CH 16:42"}, "and with them Heman and Jeduthun with trumpets and cymbals for those that should sound aloud, and with instruments for\nthe songs of Allah; and the sons of Jeduthun to be at the gate. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1CH 16:43"}, "All the people departed, each man to his house; and Dawood returned to bless his house.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 17"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 17:1"}, "When Dawood lived in his house, Dawood said to Nathan the prophet, \u201cBehold, I dwell in a house of cedar, but the ark of\nthe LORD\u2019s covenant is in a tent.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 17:2"}, "Nathan said to Dawood, \u201cDo all that is in your heart; for Allah is with you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 17:3"}, "That same night, the word of Allah came to Nathan, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 17:4"}, "\u201cGo and tell Dawood my servant, \u2018The LORD says, \u201cYou shall not build me a house to dwell in;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 17:5"}, "for I have not lived in a house since the day that I brought up Israel to this day, but have gone from tent to tent, and\nfrom one tent to another. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 17:6"}, "In all places in which I have walked with all Israel, did I speak a word with any of the judges of Israel, whom I\ncommanded to be shepherd of my people, saying, \u2018Why have you not built me a house of cedar?\u2019\u201d\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 17:7"}, "\u201cNow therefore, you shall tell my servant Dawood, \u2018The LORD of Armies says, \u201cI took you from the sheep pen, from following\nthe sheep, to be prince over my people Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 17:8"}, "I have been with you wherever you have gone, and have cut off all your enemies from before you. I will make you a name\nlike the name of the great ones who are in the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 17:9"}, "I will appoint a place for my people Israel, and will plant them, that they may dwell in their own place, and be moved no\nmore. The children of wickedness will not waste them any more, as at the first,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 17:10"}, "and from the day that I commanded judges to be over my people Israel. I will subdue all your enemies. Moreover I tell you\nthat the LORD will build you a house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 17:11"}, "It will happen, when your days are fulfilled that you must go to be with your fathers, that I will set up your offspring\nafter you, who will be of your sons; and I will establish his kingdom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 17:12"}, "He will build me a house, and I will establish his throne forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 17:13"}, "I will be his father, and he will be my son. I will not take my loving kindness away from him, as I took it from him that\nwas before you; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 17:14"}, "but I will settle him in my house and in my kingdom forever. His throne will be established forever.\u201d\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 17:15"}, "According to all these words, and according to all this vision, so Nathan spoke to Dawood.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 17:16"}, "Then Dawood the king went in, and sat before the LORD; and he said, \u201cWho am I, Allah the LORD, and what is my house, that\nyou have brought me this far? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 17:17"}, "This was a small thing in your eyes, Allah; but you have spoken of your servant\u2019s house for a great while to come, and\nhave respected me according to the standard of a man of high degree, Allah the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 17:18"}, "What can Dawood say yet more to you concerning the honour which is done to your servant? For you know your servant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 17:19"}, "LORD, for your servant\u2019s sake, and according to your own heart, you have done all this greatness, to make known all these\ngreat things. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 17:20"}, "LORD, there is no one like you, neither is there any Allah besides you, according to all that we have heard with our\nears. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 17:21"}, "What one nation in the earth is like your people Israel, whom Allah went to redeem to himself for a people, to make you a\nname by great and awesome things, in driving out nations from before your people, whom you redeem out of Egypt?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 17:22"}, "For you made your people Israel your own people forever; and you, LORD, became their Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 17:23"}, "Now, LORD, let the word that you have spoken concerning your servant, and concerning his house, be established forever,\nand do as you have spoken. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 17:24"}, "Let your name be established and magnified forever, saying, \u2018The LORD of Armies is Allah of Israel, even Allah to Israel.\nThe house of Dawood your servant is established before you.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 17:25"}, "For you, my Allah, have revealed to your servant that you will build him a house. Therefore your servant has found\ncourage to pray before you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 17:26"}, "Now, LORD, you are Allah, and have promised this good thing to your servant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 17:27"}, "Now it has pleased you to bless the house of your servant, that it may continue forever before you; for you, LORD, have\nblessed, and it is blessed forever.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 18"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 18:1"}, "After this, Dawood defeated the Philistines and subdued them, and took Gath and its towns out of the hand of the\nPhilistines. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 18:2"}, "He defeated Moab; and the Moabites became servants to Dawood, and brought tribute.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 18:3"}, "Dawood defeated Hadadezer king of Zobah to Hamath, as he went to establish his dominion by the river Euphrates.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 18:4"}, "Dawood took from him one thousand chariots, seven thousand horsemen, and twenty thousand footmen; and Dawood hamstrung all\nthe chariot horses, but reserved of them enough for one hundred chariots.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 18:5"}, "When the Syrians of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king of Zobah, Dawood struck twenty-two thousand men of the Syrians.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 18:6"}, "Then Dawood put garrisons in Syria of Damascus; and the Syrians became servants to Dawood, and brought tribute. The LORD\ngave victory to Dawood wherever he went. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 18:7"}, "Dawood took the shields of gold that were on the servants of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 18:8"}, "From Tibhath and from Cun, cities of Hadadezer, Dawood took very much bronze, with which Sulaiman made the bronze sea, the\npillars, and the vessels of bronze. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 18:9"}, "When Tou king of Hamath heard that Dawood had struck all the army of Hadadezer king of Zobah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 18:10"}, "he sent Hadoram his son to king Dawood, to Greet him, and to bless him, because he had fought against Hadadezer and\nstruck him (for Hadadezer had wars with Tou); and he had with him all kinds of vessels of gold and silver and bronze.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 18:11"}, "King Dawood also dedicated these to the LORD, with the silver and the gold that he carried away from all the nations;\nfrom Edom, from Moab, from the children of Ammon, from the Philistines, and from Amalek.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 18:12"}, "Moreover Abishai the son of Zeruiah struck eighteen thousand of the Edomites in the Valley of Salt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 18:13"}, "He put garrisons in Edom; and all the Edomites became servants to Dawood. The LORD gave victory to Dawood wherever he\nwent. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 18:14"}, "Dawood reigned over all Israel; and he executed justice and righteousness for all his people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 18:15"}, "Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the army; Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was recorder;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 18:16"}, "Zadok the son of Ahitub, and Abimelech the son of Abiathar, were priests; Shavsha was scribe;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 18:17"}, "and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites; and the sons of Dawood were chief officials\nserving the king. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 19"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 19:1"}, "After this, Nahash the king of the children of Ammon died, and his son reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 19:2"}, "Dawood said, \u201cI will show kindness to Hanun the son of Nahash, because his father showed kindness to me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["So Dawood sent messengers to comfort him concerning his father. Dawood\u2019s servants came into the land of the children of\nAmmon to Hanun, to comfort him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 19:3"}, "But the princes of the children of Ammon said to Hanun, \u201cDo you think that Dawood honours your father, in that he has sent\ncomforters to you? Haven\u2019t his servants come to you to search, to overthrow, and to spy out the land?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 19:4"}, "So Hanun took Dawood\u2019s servants, shaved them, and cut off their garments in the middle at their buttocks, and sent them\naway. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 19:5"}, "Then some people went and told Dawood how the men were treated. He sent to meet them; for the men were greatly humiliated.\nThe king said, \u201cStay at Jericho until your beards have grown, and then return.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 19:6"}, "When the children of Ammon saw that they had made themselves odious to Dawood, Hanun and the children of Ammon sent one\nthousand talents", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["19:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds, so 1000 talents is about 30 metric\ntonnes"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of silver to hire chariots and horsemen out of Mesopotamia, out of Aram-maacah, and out of Zobah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 19:7"}, "So they hired for themselves thirty-two thousand chariots, and the king of Maacah with his people, who came and encamped\nnear Medeba. The children of Ammon gathered themselves together from their cities, and came to battle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 19:8"}, "When Dawood heard of it, he sent Joab with all the army of the mighty men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 19:9"}, "The children of Ammon came out, and put the battle in array at the gate of the city; and the kings who had come were by\nthemselves in the field. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 19:10"}, "Now when Joab saw that the battle was set against him before and behind, he chose some of all the choice men of Israel,\nand put them in array against the Syrians. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 19:11"}, "The rest of the people he committed into the hand of Abishai his brother; and they put themselves in array against the\nchildren of Ammon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 19:12"}, "He said, \u201cIf the Syrians are too strong for me, then you are to help me; but if the children of Ammon are too strong for\nyou, then I will help you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 19:13"}, "Be courageous, and let\u2019s be strong for our people and for the cities of our Allah. May the LORD do that which seems good\nto him.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 19:14"}, "So Joab and the people who were with him came near to the front of the Syrians to the battle; and they fled before him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 19:15"}, "When the children of Ammon saw that the Syrians had fled, they likewise fled before Abishai his brother, and entered into\nthe city. Then Joab came to Jerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 19:16"}, "When the Syrians saw that they were defeated by Israel, they sent messengers, and called out the Syrians who were beyond\nthe River,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["19:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, the Euphrates River"]}], "caller": "+"}, " with Shophach the captain of the army of Hadadezer leading them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 19:17"}, "Dawood was told that; so he gathered all Israel together, passed over the Jordan, came to them, and set the battle in\narray against them. So when Dawood had put the battle in array against the Syrians, they fought with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 19:18"}, "The Syrians fled before Israel; and Dawood killed of the Syrian men seven thousand chariots, and forty thousand footmen,\nand also killed Shophach the captain of the army. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 19:19"}, "When the servants of Hadadezer saw that they were defeated by Israel, they made peace with Dawood, and served him. The\nSyrians would not help the children of Ammon any more. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 20"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 20:1"}, "At the time of the return of the year, at the time when kings go out, Joab led out the army, and wasted the country of the\nchildren of Ammon, and came and besieged Rabbah. But Dawood stayed at Jerusalem. Joab struck Rabbah, and overthrew it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 20:2"}, "Dawood took the crown of their king from off his head, and found it to weigh a talent of\ngold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy\nounces"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and there were precious stones in it. It was set on Dawood\u2019s head, and he brought very much plunder out of the city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 20:3"}, "He brought out the people who were in it, and had them cut with saws, with iron picks, and with axes. Dawood did so to all\nthe cities of the children of Ammon. Then Dawood and all the people returned to Jerusalem.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 20:4"}, "After this, war arose at Gezer with the Philistines. Then Sibbecai the Hushathite killed Sippai, of the sons of the giant;\nand they were subdued. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 20:5"}, "Again there was war with the Philistines; and Elhanan the son of Jair killed Lahmi the brother of Goliath the Gittite, the\nstaff of whose spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 20:6"}, "There was again war at Gath, where there was a man of great stature, who had twenty-four fingers and toes, six on each\nhand, and six on each foot; and he also was born to the giant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 20:7"}, "When he defied Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimea Dawood\u2019s brother killed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 20:8"}, "These were born to the giant in Gath; and they fell by the hand of Dawood, and by the hand of his servants.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 21"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 21:1"}, "Iblis stood up against Israel, and moved Dawood to take a census of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 21:2"}, "Dawood said to Joab and to the princes of the people, \u201cGo, count Israel from Beersheba even to Dan; and bring me word,\nthat I may know how many there are.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 21:3"}, "Joab said, \u201cMay the LORD make his people a hundred times as many as they are. But, my lord the king, aren\u2019t they all my\nlord\u2019s servants? Why does my lord require this thing? Why will he be a cause of guilt to Israel?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 21:4"}, "Nevertheless the king\u2019s word prevailed against Joab. Therefore Joab departed, and went throughout all Israel, then came to\nJerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 21:5"}, "Joab gave up the sum of the census of the people to Dawood. All those of Israel were one million one hundred thousand men\nwho drew a sword; and in Judah were four hundred and seventy thousand men who drew a sword.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 21:6"}, "But he didn\u2019t count Levi and Benjamin amongst them; for the king\u2019s word was abominable to Joab.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 21:7"}, "Allah was displeased with this thing; therefore he struck Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 21:8"}, "Dawood said to Allah, \u201cI have sinned greatly, in that I have done this thing. But now put away, I beg you, the iniquity of\nyour servant; for I have done very foolishly.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 21:9"}, "The LORD spoke to Gad, Dawood\u2019s seer, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 21:10"}, "\u201cGo and speak to Dawood, saying, \u2018The LORD says, \u201cI offer you three things. Choose one of them, that I may do it to\nyou.\u201d\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 21:11"}, "So Gad came to Dawood, and said to him, \u201cThe LORD says, \u2018Take your choice:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 21:12"}, "either three years of famine; or three months to be consumed before your foes, while the sword of your enemies overtakes\nyou; or else three days the sword of the LORD, even pestilence in the land, and the LORD\u2019s angel destroying throughout all the\nborders of Israel. Now therefore consider what answer I shall return to him who sent me.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 21:13"}, "Dawood said to Gad, \u201cI am in distress. Let me fall, I pray, into the LORD\u2019s hand; for his mercies are very great. Don\u2019t\nlet me fall into man\u2019s hand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 21:14"}, "So the LORD sent a pestilence on Israel, and seventy thousand men of Israel fell.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 21:15"}, "Allah sent an angel to Jerusalem to destroy it. As he was about to destroy, the LORD saw, and he relented of the\ndisaster, and said to the destroying angel, \u201cIt is enough. Now withdraw your hand.\u201d the LORD\u2019s angel was standing by the\nthreshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 21:16"}, "Dawood lifted up his eyes, and saw the LORD\u2019s angel standing between earth and the sky, having a drawn sword in his hand\nstretched out over Jerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then Dawood and the elders, clothed in sackcloth, fell on their faces.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 21:17"}, "Dawood said to Allah, \u201cIsn\u2019t it I who commanded the people to be counted? It is even I who have sinned and done very\nwickedly; but these sheep, what have they done? Please let your hand, O LORD my Allah, be against me, and against my father\u2019s\nhouse; but not against your people, that they should be plagued.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 21:18"}, "Then the LORD\u2019s angel commanded Gad to tell Dawood that Dawood should go up and raise an altar to the LORD on the\nthreshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 21:19"}, "Dawood went up at the saying of Gad, which he spoke in the LORD\u2019s name.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 21:20"}, "Ornan turned back, and saw the angel; and his four sons who were with him hid themselves. Now Ornan was threshing wheat.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 21:21"}, "As Dawood came to Ornan, Ornan looked and saw Dawood, and went out of the threshing floor, and bowed himself to Dawood\nwith his face to the ground. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 21:22"}, "Then Dawood said to Ornan, \u201cGive me the place of this threshing floor, that I may build an altar to the LORD on it. You\nshall sell it to me for the full price, that the plague may be stopped from afflicting the people.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 21:23"}, "Ornan said to Dawood, \u201cTake it for yourself, and let my lord the king do that which is good in his eyes. Behold, I give\nthe oxen for burnt offerings, and the threshing instruments for wood, and the wheat for the meal offering. I give it all.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 21:24"}, "King Dawood said to Ornan, \u201cNo; but I will most certainly buy it for the full price. For I will not take that which is\nyours for the LORD, nor offer a burnt offering that costs me nothing.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 21:25"}, "So Dawood gave to Ornan six hundred shekels", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["21:25\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.32 Troy ounces, so 600 shekels was about 6 kilograms or about 192 Troy\nounces."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of gold by weight for the place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 21:26"}, "Dawood built an altar to the LORD there, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings, and called on the LORD; and he\nanswered him from the sky by fire on the altar of burnt offering.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 21:27"}, "Then The LORD commanded the angel, and he put his sword back into its sheath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 21:28"}, "At that time, when Dawood saw that the LORD had answered him in the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite, then he\nsacrificed there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 21:29"}, "For the LORD\u2019s tabernacle, which Musa made in the wilderness, and the altar of burnt offering, were at that time in the\nhigh place at Gibeon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 21:30"}, "But Dawood couldn\u2019t go before it to enquire of Allah; for he was afraid because of the sword of the LORD\u2019s angel.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 22"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 22:1"}, "Then Dawood said, \u201cThis is the house of the LORD Allah, and this is the altar of burnt offering for Israel.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 22:2"}, "Dawood gave orders to gather together the foreigners who were in the land of Israel; and he set masons to cut dressed\nstones to build Allah\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 22:3"}, "Dawood prepared iron in abundance for the nails for the doors of the gates, and for the couplings; and bronze in abundance\nwithout weight; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 22:4"}, "and cedar trees without number, for the Sidonians and the people of Tyre brought cedar trees in abundance to Dawood.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 22:5"}, "Dawood said, \u201cSulaiman my son is young and tender, and the house that is to be built for the LORD must be exceedingly\nmagnificent, of fame and of glory throughout all countries. I will therefore make preparation for it.\u201d So Dawood prepared\nabundantly before his death. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 22:6"}, "Then he called for Sulaiman his son, and commanded him to build a house for the LORD, Allah of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 22:7"}, "Dawood said to Sulaiman his son, \u201cAs for me, it was in my heart to build a house to the name of the LORD my Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 22:8"}, "But the LORD\u2019s word came to me, saying, \u2018You have shed blood abundantly, and have made great wars. You shall not build a\nhouse to my name, because you have shed much blood on the earth in my sight.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 22:9"}, "Behold, a son shall be born to you, who shall be a man of peace. I will give him rest from all his enemies all around; for\nhis name shall be Sulaiman, and I will give peace and quietness to Israel in his days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 22:10"}, "He shall build a house for my name; and he will be my son, and I will be his father; and I will establish the throne of\nhis kingdom over Israel forever.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 22:11"}, "Now, my son, may the LORD be with you and prosper you, and build the house of Allah your LORD, as he has spoken\nconcerning you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 22:12"}, "May the LORD give you discretion and understanding, and put you in charge of Israel; that so you may keep the law of\nAllah your LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 22:13"}, "Then you will prosper, if you observe to do the statutes and the ordinances which the LORD gave Musa concerning Israel.\nBe strong and courageous. Don\u2019t be afraid, and don\u2019t be dismayed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 22:14"}, "Now, behold, in my affliction I have prepared for the LORD\u2019s house one hundred thousand\ntalents", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["22:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy ounces, so 100,000 talents is about 3 metric\ntonnes"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of gold, one million talents", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["22:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["about 30,000 metric\ntonnes"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of silver, and bronze and iron without weight; for it is in abundance. I have also prepared timber and stone; and you\nmay add to them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 22:15"}, "There are also workmen with you in abundance, cutters and workers of stone and timber, and all kinds of men who are\nskilful in every kind of work; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 22:16"}, "of the gold, the silver, the bronze, and the iron, there is no number. Arise and be doing, and may the LORD be with you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 22:17"}, "Dawood also commanded all the princes of Israel to help Sulaiman his son, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 22:18"}, "\u201cIsn\u2019t Allah your LORD with you? Hasn\u2019t he given you rest on every side? For he has delivered the inhabitants of the land\ninto my hand; and the land is subdued before the LORD, and before his people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 22:19"}, "Now set your heart and your soul to follow Allah your LORD. Arise therefore, and build the sanctuary of the LORD Allah,\nto bring the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant and the holy vessels of Allah into the house that is to be built for the LORD\u2019s name.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 23"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 23:1"}, "Now Dawood was old and full of days; and he made Sulaiman his son king over Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 23:2"}, "He gathered together all the princes of Israel, with the priests and the Levites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 23:3"}, "The Levites were counted from thirty years old and upward; and their number by their polls, man by man, was thirty-eight\nthousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 23:4"}, "Dawood said, \u201cOf these, twenty-four thousand were to oversee the work of the LORD\u2019s house, six thousand were officers and\njudges, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 23:5"}, "four thousand were doorkeepers, and four thousand praised the LORD with the instruments which I made for giving praise.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 23:6"}, "Dawood divided them into divisions according to the sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 23:7"}, "Of the Gershonites: Ladan and Shimei. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 23:8"}, "The sons of Ladan: Jehiel the chief, Zetham, and Joel, three.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 23:9"}, "The sons of Shimei: Shelomoth, Haziel, and Haran, three. These were the heads of the fathers\u2019 households of Ladan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 23:10"}, "The sons of Shimei: Jahath, Zina, Jeush, and Beriah. These four were the sons of Shimei.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 23:11"}, "Jahath was the chief, and Zizah the second; but Jeush and Beriah didn\u2019t have many sons; therefore they became a fathers\u2019\nhouse in one reckoning. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 23:12"}, "The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel, four.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 23:13"}, "The sons of Amram: Harun and Musa; and Harun was separated, that he should sanctify the most holy things, he and his\nsons, forever, to burn incense before the LORD, to minister to him, and to bless in his name, forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 23:14"}, "But as for Musa the man of Allah, his sons were named amongst the tribe of Levi.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 23:15"}, "The sons of Musa: Gershom and Eliezer. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 23:16"}, "The sons of Gershom: Shebuel the chief. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 23:17"}, "The sons of Eliezer were: Rehabiah the chief; and Eliezer had no other sons; but the sons of Rehabiah were very many.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 23:18"}, "The sons of Izhar: Shelomith the chief. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 23:19"}, "The sons of Hebron: Jeriah the chief, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, and Jekameam the fourth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 23:20"}, "The sons of Uzziel: Micah the chief, and Isshiah the second.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 23:21"}, "The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. The sons of Mahli: Eleazar and Kish.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 23:22"}, "Eleazar died, and had no sons, but daughters only: and their brothers the sons of Kish took them as wives.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 23:23"}, "The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jeremoth, three. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 23:24"}, "These were the sons of Levi after their fathers\u2019 houses, even the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses of those who were counted\nindividually, in the number of names by their polls, who did the work for the service of the LORD\u2019s house, from twenty years\nold and upward. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 23:25"}, "For Dawood said, \u201cThe LORD, Allah of Israel, has given rest to his people; and he dwells in Jerusalem forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 23:26"}, "Also the Levites will no longer need to carry the tabernacle and all its vessels for its service.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 23:27"}, "For by the last words of Dawood the sons of Levi were counted, from twenty years old and upward.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 23:28"}, "For their office was to wait on the sons of Harun for the service of the LORD\u2019s house, in the courts, and in the rooms,\nand in the purifying of all holy things, even the work of the service of Allah\u2019s house;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 23:29"}, "for the show bread also, and for the fine flour for a meal offering, whether of unleavened wafers, or of that which is\nbaked in the pan, or of that which is soaked, and for all measurements of quantity and size;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 23:30"}, "and to stand every morning to thank and praise the LORD, and likewise in the evening;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 23:31"}, "and to offer all burnt offerings to the LORD, on the Sabbaths, on the new moons, and on the set feasts, in number\naccording to the ordinance concerning them, continually before the LORD;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 23:32"}, "and that they should keep the duty of the Tent of Meeting, the duty of the holy place, and the duty of the sons of Harun\ntheir brothers, for the service of the LORD\u2019s house. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 24"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 24:1"}, "These were the divisions of the sons of Harun. The sons of Harun: Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 24:2"}, "But Nadab and Abihu died before their father, and had no children: therefore Eleazar and Ithamar executed the priest\u2019s\noffice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 24:3"}, "Dawood with Zadok of the sons of Eleazar and Ahimelech of the sons of Ithamar, divided them according to their ordering in\ntheir service. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 24:4"}, "There were more chief men found of the sons of Eleazar than of the sons of Ithamar; and they were divided like this: of\nthe sons of Eleazar there were sixteen, heads of fathers\u2019 houses; and of the sons of Ithamar, according to their fathers\u2019\nhouses, eight. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 24:5"}, "Thus they were divided impartially by drawing lots; for there were princes of the sanctuary, and princes of Allah, both of\nthe sons of Eleazar, and of the sons of Ithamar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 24:6"}, "Shemaiah the son of Nethanel the scribe, who was of the Levites, wrote them in the presence of the king, the princes,\nZadok the priest, Ahimelech the son of Abiathar, and the heads of the fathers\u2019 households of the priests and of the Levites;\none fathers\u2019 house being taken for Eleazar, and one taken for Ithamar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 24:7"}, "Now the first lot came out to Jehoiarib, the second to Jedaiah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 24:8"}, "the third to Harim, the fourth to Seorim, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 24:9"}, "the fifth to Malchijah, the sixth to Mijamin, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 24:10"}, "the seventh to Hakkoz, the eighth to Abijah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 24:11"}, "the ninth to Jeshua, the tenth to Shecaniah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 24:12"}, "the eleventh to Eliashib, the twelfth to Jakim, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 24:13"}, "the thirteenth to Huppah, the fourteenth to Jeshebeab, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 24:14"}, "the fifteenth to Bilgah, the sixteenth to Immer, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 24:15"}, "the seventeenth to Hezir, the eighteenth to Happizzez, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 24:16"}, "the nineteenth to Pethahiah, the twentieth to Jehezkel, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 24:17"}, "the twenty-first to Jachin, the twenty-second to Gamul, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 24:18"}, "the twenty-third to Delaiah, and the twenty-fourth to Maaziah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 24:19"}, "This was their ordering in their service, to come into the LORD\u2019s house according to the ordinance given to them by Harun\ntheir father, as the LORD, Allah of Israel, had commanded him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 24:20"}, "Of the rest of the sons of Levi: of the sons of Amram, Shubael; of the sons of Shubael, Jehdeiah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 24:21"}, "Of Rehabiah: of the sons of Rehabiah, Isshiah the chief. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 24:22"}, "Of the Izharites, Shelomoth; of the sons of Shelomoth, Jahath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 24:23"}, "The sons of Hebron: Jeriah, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, and Jekameam the fourth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 24:24"}, "The sons of Uzziel: Micah; of the sons of Micah, Shamir. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 24:25"}, "The brother of Micah: Isshiah; of the sons of Isshiah, Zakariya.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 24:26"}, "The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. The son of Jaaziah: Beno.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 24:27"}, "The sons of Merari: of Jaaziah, Beno, Shoham, Zaccur, and Ibri.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 24:28"}, "Of Mahli: Eleazar, who had no sons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 24:29"}, "Of Kish, the son of Kish: Jerahmeel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 24:30"}, "The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jerimoth. These were the sons of the Levites after their fathers\u2019 houses.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 24:31"}, "These likewise cast lots even as their brothers the sons of Harun in the presence of Dawood the king, Zadok, Ahimelech,\nand the heads of the fathers\u2019 households of the priests and of the Levites; the fathers\u2019 households of the chief even as those\nof his younger brother. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 25"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 25:1"}, "Moreover, Dawood and the captains of the army set apart for the service certain of the sons of Asaph, and of Heman, and of\nJeduthun, who were to prophesy with harps, with stringed instruments, and with cymbals. The number of those who did the work\naccording to their service was: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 25:2"}, "of the sons of Asaph: Zaccur, Yusuf, Nethaniah, and Asharelah. The sons of Asaph were under the hand of Asaph, who\nprophesied at the order of the king. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 25:3"}, "Of Jeduthun, the sons of Jeduthun: Gedaliah, Zeri, Jeshaiah, Shimei, Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six, under the hands of\ntheir father Jeduthun, who prophesied in giving thanks and praising the LORD with the harp.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 25:4"}, "Of Heman, the sons of Heman: Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel, Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti,\nRomamti-Ezer, Joshbekashah, Mallothi, Hothir, and Mahazioth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 25:5"}, "All these were the sons of Heman the king\u2019s seer in the words of Allah, to lift up the horn. Allah gave to Heman fourteen\nsons and three daughters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 25:6"}, "All these were under the hands of their father for song in the LORD\u2019s house, with cymbals, stringed instruments, and\nharps, for the service of Allah\u2019s house: Asaph, Jeduthun, and Heman being under the order of the king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 25:7"}, "The number of them, with their brothers who were instructed in singing to the LORD, even all who were skilful, was two\nhundred and eighty-eight. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 25:8"}, "They cast lots for their offices, all alike, the small as well as the great, the teacher as well as the student.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 25:9"}, "Now the first lot came out for Asaph to Yusuf; the second to Gedaliah, he and his brothers and sons were twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 25:10"}, "the third to Zaccur, his sons and his brothers, twelve; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 25:11"}, "the fourth to Izri, his sons and his brothers, twelve; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 25:12"}, "the fifth to Nethaniah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 25:13"}, "the sixth to Bukkiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 25:14"}, "the seventh to Jesharelah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 25:15"}, "the eighth to Jeshaiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 25:16"}, "the ninth to Mattaniah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 25:17"}, "the tenth to Shimei, his sons and his brothers, twelve; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 25:18"}, "the eleventh to Azarel, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 25:19"}, "the twelfth to Hashabiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 25:20"}, "for the thirteenth, Shubael, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 25:21"}, "for the fourteenth, Mattithiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 25:22"}, "for the fifteenth to Jeremoth, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 25:23"}, "for the sixteenth to Hananiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 25:24"}, "for the seventeenth to Joshbekashah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 25:25"}, "for the eighteenth to Hanani, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 25:26"}, "for the nineteenth to Mallothi, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 25:27"}, "for the twentieth to Eliathah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 25:28"}, "for the twenty-first to Hothir, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 25:29"}, "for the twenty-second to Giddalti, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 25:30"}, "for the twenty-third to Mahazioth, his sons and his brothers, twelve;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 25:31"}, "for the twenty-fourth to Romamti-Ezer, his sons and his brothers, twelve.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 26"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 26:1"}, "For the divisions of the doorkeepers: of the Korahites, Meshelemiah the son of Kore, of the sons of Asaph.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 26:2"}, "Meshelemiah had sons: Zakariya the firstborn, Jediael the second, Zebadiah the third, Jathniel the fourth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 26:3"}, "Elam the fifth, Jehohanan the sixth, and Eliehoenai the seventh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 26:4"}, "Obed-Edom had sons: Shemaiah the firstborn, Jehozabad the second, Joah the third, Sacar the fourth, Nethanel the fifth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 26:5"}, "Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh, and Peullethai the eighth; for Allah blessed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 26:6"}, "Sons were also born to Shemaiah his son, who ruled over the house of their father; for they were mighty men of valour.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 26:7"}, "The sons of Shemaiah: Othni, Rephael, Obed, and Elzabad, whose brothers were valiant men, Elihu, and Semachiah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 26:8"}, "All these were of the sons of Obed-Edom: they and their sons and their brothers, able men in strength for the service:\nsixty-two of Obed-Edom. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 26:9"}, "Meshelemiah had sons and brothers, valiant men, eighteen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 26:10"}, "Also Hosah, of the children of Merari, had sons: Shimri the chief (for though he was not the firstborn, yet his father\nmade him chief), \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 26:11"}, "Hilkiah the second, Tebaliah the third, and Zakariya the fourth. All the sons and brothers of Hosah were thirteen.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 26:12"}, "Of these were the divisions of the doorkeepers, even of the chief men, having offices like their brothers, to minister in\nthe LORD\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 26:13"}, "They cast lots, the small as well as the great, according to their fathers\u2019 houses, for every gate.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 26:14"}, "The lot eastward fell to Shelemiah. Then for Zakariya his son, a wise counsellor, they cast lots; and his lot came out\nnorthward. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 26:15"}, "To Obed-Edom southward; and to his sons the storehouse. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 26:16"}, "To Shuppim and Hosah westward, by the gate of Shallecheth, at the causeway that goes up, watchman opposite watchman.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 26:17"}, "Eastward were six Levites, northward four a day, southward four a day, and for the storehouse two and two.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 26:18"}, "For Parbar westward, four at the causeway, and two at Parbar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 26:19"}, "These were the divisions of the doorkeepers; of the sons of the Korahites, and of the sons of Merari.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 26:20"}, "Of the Levites, Ahijah was over the treasures of Allah\u2019s house and over the treasures of the dedicated things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 26:21"}, "The sons of Ladan, the sons of the Gershonites belonging to Ladan, the heads of the fathers\u2019 households belonging to\nLadan the Gershonite: Jehieli. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 26:22"}, "The sons of Jehieli: Zetham, and Joel his brother, over the treasures of the LORD\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 26:23"}, "Of the Amramites, of the Izharites, of the Hebronites, of the Uzzielites:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 26:24"}, "and Shebuel the son of Gershom, the son of Musa, was ruler over the treasures.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 26:25"}, "His brothers: of Eliezer, Rehabiah his son, and Jeshaiah his son, and Joram his son, and Zichri his son, and Shelomoth\nhis son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 26:26"}, "This Shelomoth and his brothers were over all the treasures of the dedicated things, which Dawood the king, and the heads\nof the fathers\u2019 households, the captains over thousands and hundreds, and the captains of the army, had dedicated.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 26:27"}, "They dedicated some of the plunder won in battles to repair the LORD\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 26:28"}, "All that Samuel the seer, and Saul the son of Kish, and Abner the son of Ner, and Joab the son of Zeruiah, had dedicated,\nwhoever had dedicated anything, it was under the hand of Shelomoth, and of his brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 26:29"}, "Of the Izharites, Chenaniah and his sons were for the outward business over Israel, for officers and judges.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 26:30"}, "Of the Hebronites, Hashabiah and his brothers, men of valour, one thousand and seven hundred, had the oversight of Israel\nbeyond the Jordan westward, for all the business of the LORD, and for the service of the king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 26:31"}, "Of the Hebronites, Jerijah was the chief, even of the Hebronites, according to their generations by fathers\u2019 households.\nThey were sought for in the fortieth year of the reign of Dawood, and mighty men of valour were found amongst them at Jazer of\nGilead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 26:32"}, "His brothers, men of valour, were two thousand and seven hundred, heads of fathers\u2019 households, whom king Dawood made\noverseers over the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of the Manassites, for every matter pertaining to Allah, and for\nthe affairs of the king. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 27"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 27:1"}, "Now the children of Israel after their number, the heads of fathers\u2019 households and the captains of thousands and of\nhundreds, and their officers who served the king, in any matter of the divisions which came in and went out month by month\nthroughout all the months of the year\u2014of every division were twenty-four thousand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 27:2"}, "Over the first division for the first month was Jashobeam the son of Zabdiel: and in his division were twenty-four\nthousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 27:3"}, "He was of the children of Perez, the chief of all the captains of the army for the first month.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 27:4"}, "Over the division of the second month was Dodai the Ahohite, and his division; and Mikloth the ruler: and in his division\nwere twenty-four thousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 27:5"}, "The third captain of the army for the third month was Benaiah, the son of Jehoiada the chief priest. In his division were\ntwenty-four thousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 27:6"}, "This is that Benaiah who was the mighty man of the thirty, and over the thirty: and of his division was Ammizabad his son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 27:7"}, "The fourth captain for the fourth month was Asahel the brother of Joab, and Zebadiah his son after him: and in his\ndivision were twenty-four thousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 27:8"}, "The fifth captain for the fifth month was Shamhuth the Izrahite: and in his division were twenty-four thousand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 27:9"}, "The sixth captain for the sixth month was Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite: and in his division were twenty-four\nthousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 27:10"}, "The seventh captain for the seventh month was Helez the Pelonite, of the children of Ephraim. In his division were\ntwenty-four thousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 27:11"}, "The eighth captain for the eighth month was Sibbecai the Hushathite, of the Zerahites. In his division were twenty-four\nthousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 27:12"}, "The ninth captain for the ninth month was Abiezer the Anathothite, of the Benjamites. In his division were twenty-four\nthousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 27:13"}, "The tenth captain for the tenth month was Maharai the Netophathite, of the Zerahites. In his division were twenty-four\nthousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 27:14"}, "The eleventh captain for the eleventh month was Benaiah the Pirathonite, of the children of Ephraim. In his division were\ntwenty-four thousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 27:15"}, "The twelfth captain for the twelfth month was Heldai the Netophathite, of Othniel. In his division were twenty-four\nthousand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 27:16"}, "Furthermore over the tribes of Israel: of the Reubenites, Eliezer the son of Zichri was the ruler; of the Simeonites,\nShephatiah the son of Maacah; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 27:17"}, "of Levi, Hashabiah the son of Kemuel; of Harun, Zadok; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 27:18"}, "of Judah, Elihu, one of the brothers of Dawood; of Issachar, Omri the son of Michael;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 27:19"}, "of Zebulun, Ishmaiah the son of Obadiah; of Naphtali, Jeremoth the son of Azriel;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 27:20"}, "of the children of Ephraim, Hoshea the son of Azaziah; of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Joel the son of Pedaiah;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 27:21"}, "of the half-tribe of Manasseh in Gilead, Iddo the son of Zakariya; of Benjamin, Jaasiel the son of Abner;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 27:22"}, "of Dan, Azarel the son of Jeroham. These were the captains of the tribes of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 27:23"}, "But Dawood didn\u2019t take the number of them from twenty years old and under, because the LORD had said he would increase\nIsrael like the stars of the sky. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 27:24"}, "Joab the son of Zeruiah began to take a census, but didn\u2019t finish; and wrath came on Israel for this. The number wasn\u2019t\nput into the account in the chronicles of king Dawood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 27:25"}, "Over the king\u2019s treasures was Azmaveth the son of Adiel: and over the treasures in the fields, in the cities, and in the\nvillages, and in the towers, was Jonathan the son of Uzziah; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 27:26"}, "Over those who did the work of the field for tillage of the ground was Ezri the son of Chelub;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 27:27"}, "and over the vineyards was Shimei the Ramathite; and over the increase of the vineyards for the wine cellars was Zabdi\nthe Shiphmite; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 27:28"}, "and over the olive trees and the sycamore trees that were in the lowland was Baal Hanan the Gederite; and over the\ncellars of oil was Joash; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 27:29"}, "and over the herds that fed in Sharon was Shitrai the Sharonite; and over the herds that were in the valleys was Shaphat\nthe son of Adlai; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 27:30"}, "and over the camels was Obil the Ishmaelite; and over the donkeys was Jehdeiah the Meronothite; and over the flocks was\nJaziz the Hagrite. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CH 27:31"}, "All these were the rulers of the property which was king Dawood\u2019s.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CH 27:32"}, "Also Jonathan, Dawood\u2019s uncle, was a counsellor, a man of understanding, and a scribe. Jehiel the son of Hachmoni was\nwith the king\u2019s sons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CH 27:33"}, "Ahithophel was the king\u2019s counsellor. Hushai the Archite was the king\u2019s friend.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CH 27:34"}, "After Ahithophel was Jehoiada the son of Benaiah, and Abiathar. Joab was the captain of the king\u2019s army.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 28"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 28:1"}, "Dawood assembled all the princes of Israel, the princes of the tribes, the captains of the companies who served the king\nby division, the captains of thousands, the captains of hundreds, and the rulers over all the substance and possessions of the\nking and of his sons, with the officers and the mighty men, even all the mighty men of valour, to Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 28:2"}, "Then Dawood the king stood up on his feet, and said, \u201cHear me, my brothers, and my people! As for me, it was in my heart\nto build a house of rest for the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant, and for the footstool of our Allah; and I had prepared for the\nbuilding. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 28:3"}, "But Allah said to me, \u2018You shall not build a house for my name, because you are a man of war, and have shed blood.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 28:4"}, "However the LORD, Allah of Israel, chose me out of all the house of my father to be king over Israel forever. For he has\nchosen Judah to be prince; and in the house of Judah, the house of my father; and amongst the sons of my father he took\npleasure in me to make me king over all Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 28:5"}, "Of all my sons (for the LORD has given me many sons), he has chosen Sulaiman my son to sit on the throne of the LORD\u2019s\nkingdom over Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 28:6"}, "He said to me, \u2018Sulaiman, your son, shall build my house and my courts; for I have chosen him to be my son, and I will be\nhis father. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 28:7"}, "I will establish his kingdom forever if he continues to do my commandments and my ordinances, as it is today.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 28:8"}, "Now therefore, in the sight of all Israel, the LORD\u2019s assembly, and in the audience of our Allah, observe and seek out all\nthe commandments of Allah your LORD; that you may possess this good land, and leave it for an inheritance to your children\nafter you forever. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 28:9"}, "You, Sulaiman my son, know Allah of your father, and serve him with a perfect heart and with a willing mind; for the LORD\nsearches all hearts, and understands all the imaginations of the thoughts. If you seek him, he will be found by you; but if you\nforsake him, he will cast you off forever. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 28:10"}, "Take heed now; for the LORD has chosen you to build a house for the sanctuary. Be strong, and do it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 28:11"}, "Then Dawood gave to Sulaiman his son the plans for the porch of the temple, for its houses, for its treasuries, for its\nupper rooms, for its inner rooms, for the place of the mercy seat;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 28:12"}, "and the plans of all that he had by the Spirit, for the courts of the LORD\u2019s house, for all the surrounding rooms, for\nthe treasuries of Allah\u2019s house, and for the treasuries of the dedicated things;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 28:13"}, "also for the divisions of the priests and the Levites, for all the work of the service of the LORD\u2019s house, and for all\nthe vessels of service in the LORD\u2019s house; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 28:14"}, "of gold by weight for the gold, for all vessels of every kind of service; for all the vessels of silver by weight, for\nall vessels of every kind of service; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 28:15"}, "by weight also for the lamp stands of gold, and for its lamps, of gold, by weight for every lamp stand and for its lamps;\nand for the lamp stands of silver, by weight for every lamp stand and for its lamps, according to the use of every lamp stand;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 28:16"}, "and the gold by weight for the tables of show bread, for every table; and silver for the tables of silver;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 28:17"}, "and the forks, the basins, and the cups, of pure gold; and for the golden bowls by weight for every bowl; and for the\nsilver bowls by weight for every bowl; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 28:18"}, "and for the altar of incense refined gold by weight; and gold for the plans for the chariot, and the cherubim that spread\nout and cover the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 28:19"}, "\u201cAll this\u201d, Dawood said, \u201cI have been made to understand in writing from the LORD\u2019s hand, even all the works of this\npattern.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 28:20"}, "Dawood said to Sulaiman his son, \u201cBe strong and courageous, and do it. Don\u2019t be afraid, nor be dismayed; for the LORD\nAllah, even my Allah, is with you. He will not fail you, nor forsake you, until all the work for the service of the LORD\u2019s\nhouse is finished. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 28:21"}, "Behold, there are the divisions of the priests and the Levites, for all the service of Allah\u2019s house. Every willing man\nwho has skill, for any kind of service, shall be with you in all kinds of work. Also the captains and all the people will be\nentirely at your command.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 29"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CH 29:1"}, "Dawood the king said to all the assembly, \u201cSulaiman my son, whom alone Allah has chosen, is yet young and tender, and the\nwork is great; for the palace is not for man, but for the LORD Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CH 29:2"}, "Now I have prepared with all my might for the house of my Allah the gold for the things of gold, the silver for the things\nof silver, the bronze for the things of bronze, iron for the things of iron, and wood for the things of wood; also onyx stones,\nstones to be set, stones for inlaid work, of various colours, all kinds of precious stones, and marble stones in abundance.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CH 29:3"}, "In addition, because I have set my affection on the house of my Allah, since I have a treasure of my own of gold and\nsilver, I give it to the house of my Allah, over and above all that I have prepared for the holy house,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CH 29:4"}, "even three thousand talents of gold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["29:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy ounces, so\n3000 talents is about 90 metric tonnes"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of the gold of Ophir, and seven thousand\ntalents", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["29:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["about 21 metric tonnes"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of refined silver, with which to overlay the walls of the houses;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CH 29:5"}, "of gold for the things of gold, and of silver for the things of silver, and for all kinds of work to be made by the hands\nof artisans. Who then offers willingly to consecrate himself today to the LORD?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CH 29:6"}, "Then the princes of the fathers\u2019 households, and the princes of the tribes of Israel, and the captains of thousands and of\nhundreds, with the rulers over the king\u2019s work, offered willingly;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CH 29:7"}, "and they gave for the service of Allah\u2019s house of gold five thousand\ntalents", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["29:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy ounces, so 5000 talents is about 150 metric\ntonnes"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and ten thousand darics,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["29:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["a daric was a gold coin issued by a Persian king, weighing about 8.4 grams\nor about 0.27 troy ounces each."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of silver ten thousand talents, of bronze eighteen thousand talents, and of iron one hundred\nthousand talents. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CH 29:8"}, "People with whom precious stones were found gave them to the treasure of the LORD\u2019s house, under the hand of Jehiel the\nGershonite. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CH 29:9"}, "Then the people rejoiced, because they offered willingly, because with a perfect heart they offered willingly to the LORD;\nand Dawood the king also rejoiced with great joy. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CH 29:10"}, "Therefore Dawood blessed the LORD before all the assembly; and Dawood said, \u201cYou are blessed, LORD, Allah of Israel our\nfather, forever and ever. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CH 29:11"}, "Yours, LORD, is the greatness, the power, the glory, the victory, and the majesty! For all that is in the heavens and in\nthe earth is yours. Yours is the kingdom, LORD, and you are exalted as head above all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CH 29:12"}, "Both riches and honour come from you, and you rule over all! In your hand is power and might! It is in your hand to make\ngreat, and to give strength to all! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CH 29:13"}, "Now therefore, our Allah, we thank you, and praise your glorious name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CH 29:14"}, "But who am I, and what is my people, that we should be able to offer so willingly as this? For all things come from you,\nand we have given you of your own. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CH 29:15"}, "For we are strangers before you, and foreigners, as all our fathers were. Our days on the earth are as a shadow, and\nthere is no remaining. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CH 29:16"}, "LORD our Allah, all this store that we have prepared to build you a house for your holy name comes from your hand, and is\nall your own. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CH 29:17"}, "I know also, my Allah, that you try the heart, and have pleasure in uprightness. As for me, in the uprightness of my\nheart I have willingly offered all these things. Now I have seen with joy your people, who are present here, offer willingly to\nyou. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CH 29:18"}, "LORD, Allah of Ibrahim, of Is\u1e25\u0101q, and of Israel, our fathers, keep this desire forever in the thoughts of the heart of\nyour people, and prepare their heart for you; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CH 29:19"}, "and give to Sulaiman my son a perfect heart, to keep your commandments, your testimonies, and your statutes, and to do\nall these things, and to build the palace, for which I have made provision.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CH 29:20"}, "Then Dawood said to all the assembly, \u201cNow bless Allah your LORD!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the assembly blessed the LORD, Allah of their fathers, and bowed down their heads and prostrated themselves before the\nLORD and the king. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CH 29:21"}, "They sacrificed sacrifices to the LORD, and offered burnt offerings to the LORD, on the next day after that day, even one\nthousand bulls, one thousand rams, and one thousand lambs, with their drink offerings and sacrifices in abundance for all\nIsrael, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CH 29:22"}, "and ate and drank before the LORD on that day with great gladness. They made Sulaiman the son of Dawood king the second\ntime, and anointed him before the LORD to be prince, and Zadok to be priest.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CH 29:23"}, "Then Sulaiman sat on the throne of the LORD as king instead of Dawood his father, and prospered; and all Israel obeyed\nhim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CH 29:24"}, "All the princes, the mighty men, and also all of the sons of king Dawood submitted themselves to Sulaiman the king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CH 29:25"}, "The LORD magnified Sulaiman exceedingly in the sight of all Israel, and gave to him such royal majesty as had not been on\nany king before him in Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CH 29:26"}, "Now Dawood the son of Jesse reigned over all Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CH 29:27"}, "The time that he reigned over Israel was forty years; he reigned seven years in Hebron, and he reigned thirty-three years\nin Jerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CH 29:28"}, "He died at a good old age, full of days, riches, and honour; and Sulaiman his son reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CH 29:29"}, "Now the acts of Dawood the king, first and last, behold, they are written in the history of Samuel the seer, and in the\nhistory of Nathan the prophet, and in the history of Gad the seer,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CH 29:30"}, "with all his reign and his might, and the times that went over him, and over Israel, and over all the kingdoms of the\ncountries. "]}]}